343 NTSTATUS
344 ExpReadComPlusPackage (
345  VOID
346  )
347 
348 /*++
349 
350 Routine Description:
351 
352  This function reads the status of the 64-bit COM+ package from the registry
353  and stick it inside the shared page.
354 
355 Arguments:
356 
357  None.
358 
359 Return Value:
360 
361  NTSTATUS.
362 
363 --*/
364 
365 {
366  NTSTATUS Status;
367  static OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES ObjectAttributes = RTL_CONSTANT_OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES (&KeyName, OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE);
368  CHAR KeyValueBuffer[sizeof(KEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION) + sizeof(ULONG)];
369  PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION KeyValueInformation;
370  ULONG ResultLength;
371  HANDLE Key;
372 
373 
374  Status = ZwOpenKey (&Key,
375  GENERIC_READ,
376  &ObjectAttributes);
377 
378  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
379 
380  KeyValueInformation = (PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION)KeyValueBuffer;
381  Status = ZwQueryValueKey (Key,
382  &KeyValueName,
383  KeyValuePartialInformation,
384  KeyValueInformation,
385  sizeof (KeyValueBuffer),
386  &ResultLength);
387 
388  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
389 
390  if ((KeyValueInformation->Type == REG_DWORD) &&
391  (KeyValueInformation->DataLength == sizeof(ULONG))) {
392  SharedUserData->ComPlusPackage = *(PULONG)KeyValueInformation->Data;
393  }
394  }
395 
396  ZwClose (Key);
397  }
398 
399  return Status;
400 }
401 
402 NTSTATUS
403 ExpUpdateComPlusPackage (
404  IN ULONG ComPlusPackageStatus
405  )
406 
407 /*++
408 
409 Routine Description:
410 
411  This function updates the COM+ runtime package status on the system.
412  The package status indicates whether the 64-bit or the 32-bit runtime
413  should be used when executing IL_ONLY COM+ images.
414 
415 Arguments:
416 
417  ComPlusPackageStatus - COM+ Runtime package status on the system
418 
419 
420 Return Value:
421 
422  NTSTATUS
423 
424 --*/
425 
426 {
427  NTSTATUS Status;
428  static OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES ObjectAttributes = RTL_CONSTANT_OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES (&KeyName, OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE | OBJ_FORCE_ACCESS_CHECK);
429  ULONG Disposition;
430  HANDLE Key;
431 
432 
433  Status = ZwOpenKey (&Key,
434  GENERIC_WRITE,
435  &ObjectAttributes
436  );
437 
438  if (Status == STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_NOT_FOUND)
439  {
440  Status = ZwCreateKey (&Key,
441  GENERIC_WRITE,
442  &ObjectAttributes,
443  0,
444  NULL,
445  REG_OPTION_NON_VOLATILE,
446  &Disposition
447  );
448  }
449 
450  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
451 
452  Status = ZwSetValueKey (Key,
453  &KeyValueName,
454  0,
455  REG_DWORD,
456  &ComPlusPackageStatus,
457  sizeof(ULONG));
458  ZwClose (Key);
459  }
460 
461  return Status;
462 }
463 
464 NTSTATUS
465 NtQueryDefaultLocale (
466  __in BOOLEAN UserProfile,
467  __out PLCID DefaultLocaleId
468  )
469 {
470  KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode;
471  NTSTATUS Status;
472 
473  PAGED_CODE();
474 
475  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
476  try {
477 
478  //
479  // Get previous processor mode and probe output argument if necessary.
480  //
481 
482  PreviousMode = KeGetPreviousMode();
483  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
484  ProbeForWriteUlong ((PULONG)DefaultLocaleId);
485  }
486 
487  if (UserProfile) {
488  *DefaultLocaleId = MmGetSessionLocaleId ();
489  }
490  else {
491  *DefaultLocaleId = PsDefaultSystemLocaleId;
492  }
493  }
494  except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
495  Status = GetExceptionCode();
496  }
497 
498  return Status;
499 }
500 
501 NTSTATUS
502 NtSetDefaultLocale (
503  __in BOOLEAN UserProfile,
504  __in LCID DefaultLocaleId
505  )
506 {
507  NTSTATUS Status;
508  OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES ObjectAttributes;
509  UNICODE_STRING KeyPath, KeyValueName;
510  HANDLE CurrentUserKey = NULL, Key;
511  WCHAR KeyValueBuffer[ 128 ];
512  PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION KeyValueInformation;
513  ULONG ResultLength;
514  PWSTR s;
515  ULONG n, i, Digit;
516  WCHAR c;
517  ULONG Flags;
518 
519  PAGED_CODE();
520 
521  if (DefaultLocaleId & 0xFFFF0000) {
522  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
523  }
524 
525  KeyValueInformation = (PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION)KeyValueBuffer;
526  if (UserProfile) {
527  Status = RtlOpenCurrentUser( KEY_ENUMERATE_SUB_KEYS, &CurrentUserKey );
528  if (!NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
529  return Status;
530  }
531 
532  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyValueName, L"Locale" );
533  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyPath, L"Control Panel\\International" );
534  Flags = OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE | OBJ_FORCE_ACCESS_CHECK;
535  }
536  else {
537  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyValueName, L"Default" );
538  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyPath, L"\\Registry\\Machine\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Nls\\Language" );
539  CurrentUserKey = NULL;
540  Flags = OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE;
541  }
542 
543  InitializeObjectAttributes (&ObjectAttributes,
544  &KeyPath,
545  Flags,
546  CurrentUserKey,
547  NULL);
548 
549  if (DefaultLocaleId == 0) {
550 
551  Status = ZwOpenKey (&Key, GENERIC_READ, &ObjectAttributes);
552 
553  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
554  Status = ZwQueryValueKey( Key,
555  &KeyValueName,
556  KeyValuePartialInformation,
557  KeyValueInformation,
558  sizeof( KeyValueBuffer ),
559  &ResultLength
560  );
561  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
562  if (KeyValueInformation->Type == REG_SZ) {
563  s = (PWSTR)KeyValueInformation->Data;
564  for (i=0; i<KeyValueInformation->DataLength; i += sizeof( WCHAR )) {
565  c = *s++;
566  if (c >= L'0' && c <= L'9') {
567  Digit = c - L'0';
568  }
569  else if (c >= L'A' && c <= L'F') {
570  Digit = c - L'A' + 10;
571  }
572  else if (c >= L'a' && c <= L'f') {
573  Digit = c - L'a' + 10;
574  }
575  else {
576  break;
577  }
578 
579  if (Digit >= 16) {
580  break;
581  }
582 
583  DefaultLocaleId = (DefaultLocaleId << 4) | Digit;
584  }
585  }
586  else {
587  if (KeyValueInformation->Type == REG_DWORD &&
588  KeyValueInformation->DataLength == sizeof( ULONG )) {
589 
590  DefaultLocaleId = *(PLCID)KeyValueInformation->Data;
591  }
592  else {
593  Status = STATUS_UNSUCCESSFUL;
594  }
595  }
596  }
597 
598  ZwClose( Key );
599  }
600  }
601  else {
602 
603  Status = ExpValidateLocale( DefaultLocaleId );
604 
605  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
606 
607  Status = ZwOpenKey( &Key,
608  GENERIC_WRITE,
609  &ObjectAttributes
610  );
611 
612  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
613  if (UserProfile) {
614  n = 8;
615  }
616  else {
617  n = 4;
618  }
619 
620  s = &KeyValueBuffer[ n ];
621  *s-- = UNICODE_NULL;
622  i = (ULONG)DefaultLocaleId;
623 
624  while (s >= KeyValueBuffer) {
625  Digit = i & 0x0000000F;
626  if (Digit <= 9) {
627  *s-- = (WCHAR)(Digit + L'0');
628  }
629  else {
630  *s-- = (WCHAR)((Digit - 10) + L'A');
631  }
632 
633  i = i >> 4;
634  }
635 
636  Status = ZwSetValueKey( Key,
637  &KeyValueName,
638  0,
639  REG_SZ,
640  KeyValueBuffer,
641  (n+1) * sizeof( WCHAR )
642  );
643  ZwClose( Key );
644  }
645  }
646  }
647 
648  if( CurrentUserKey ) {
649  ZwClose( CurrentUserKey );
650  }
651 
652  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
653  if (UserProfile) {
654  MmSetSessionLocaleId (DefaultLocaleId);
655  }
656  else {
657  PsDefaultSystemLocaleId = DefaultLocaleId;
658  }
659  }
660 
661  return Status;
662 }
663 
664 NTSTATUS
665 NtQueryInstallUILanguage (
666  __out LANGID *InstallUILanguageId
667  )
668 {
669  KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode;
670  NTSTATUS Status;
671 
672  PAGED_CODE();
673 
674  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
675  try {
676 
677  //
678  // Get previous processor mode and probe output argument if necessary.
679  //
680 
681  PreviousMode = KeGetPreviousMode();
682  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
683  ProbeForWriteUshort( (USHORT *)InstallUILanguageId );
684  }
685 
686  *InstallUILanguageId = PsInstallUILanguageId;
687  }
688  except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
689  Status = GetExceptionCode();
690  }
691 
692  return Status;
693 }
694 
695 NTSTATUS
696 NtQueryDefaultUILanguage (
697  __out LANGID *DefaultUILanguageId
698  )
699 {
700  KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode;
701  NTSTATUS Status;
702 
703  PAGED_CODE();
704 
705  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
706  try {
707 
708  //
709  // Get previous processor mode and probe output argument if necessary.
710  //
711 
712  PreviousMode = KeGetPreviousMode();
713  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
714  ProbeForWriteUshort( (USHORT *)DefaultUILanguageId );
715  }
716 
717  //
718  // Read the UI language from the current security context.
719  //
720  if (!NT_SUCCESS(ExpGetCurrentUserUILanguage( L"MultiUILanguageId",
721  DefaultUILanguageId,
722  TRUE))) {
723  *DefaultUILanguageId = PsInstallUILanguageId;
724  }
725  }
726  except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
727  Status = GetExceptionCode();
728  }
729 
730  return Status;
731 }
732 
733 NTSTATUS
734 ExpGetUILanguagePolicy (
735  IN HANDLE CurrentUserKey,
736  OUT LANGID *PolicyUILanguageId
737  )
738 {
739  NTSTATUS Status;
740  OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES ObjectAttributes;
741  UNICODE_STRING KeyPath, KeyValueName;
742  HANDLE Key;
743  WCHAR KeyValueBuffer[ 128 ];
744  PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION KeyValueInformation;
745  ULONG ResultLength;
746  ULONG Language;
747 
748  PAGED_CODE();
749 
750  KeyValueInformation = (PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION)KeyValueBuffer;
751  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyValueName, L"MultiUILanguageId" );
752  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyPath, L"Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Control Panel\\Desktop" );
753 
754  InitializeObjectAttributes( &ObjectAttributes,
755  &KeyPath,
756  (OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE),
757  CurrentUserKey,
758  NULL
759  );
760 
761  //
762  // Check if there is a Policy key
763  //
764  Status = ZwOpenKey( &Key,
765  GENERIC_READ,
766  &ObjectAttributes
767  );
768 
769  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
770 
771  Status = ZwQueryValueKey( Key,
772  &KeyValueName,
773  KeyValuePartialInformation,
774  KeyValueInformation,
775  sizeof( KeyValueBuffer ),
776  &ResultLength
777  );
778 
779  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
780  if ((KeyValueInformation->DataLength > 2) &&
781  (KeyValueInformation->Type == REG_SZ) &&
782  ExpIsValidUILanguage((PWSTR) KeyValueInformation->Data)) {
783 
784  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyValueName, (PWSTR) KeyValueInformation->Data );
785  Status = RtlUnicodeStringToInteger( &KeyValueName,
786  (ULONG)16,
787  &Language
788  );
789  //
790  // Final check to make sure this is an MUI system
791  //
792  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
793  *PolicyUILanguageId = (LANGID)Language;
794  }
795  }
796  else {
797  Status = STATUS_UNSUCCESSFUL;
798  }
799  }
800  ZwClose( Key );
801  }
802 
803  return Status;
804 }
805 
806 NTSTATUS
807 ExpSetCurrentUserUILanguage (
808  IN WCHAR *ValueName,
809  IN LANGID CurrentUserUILanguage
810  )
811 {
812  NTSTATUS Status;
813  OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES ObjectAttributes;
814  UNICODE_STRING KeyPath, KeyValueName;
815  HANDLE CurrentUserKey, Key;
816  WCHAR KeyValueBuffer[ 128 ];
817  PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION KeyValueInformation;
818  PWSTR s;
819  ULONG i, Digit;
820 
821  PAGED_CODE();
822 
823  if (CurrentUserUILanguage & 0xFFFF0000) {
824  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
825  }
826 
827  KeyValueInformation = (PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION)KeyValueBuffer;
828  Status = RtlOpenCurrentUser( KEY_ENUMERATE_SUB_KEYS, &CurrentUserKey );
829  if (!NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
830  return Status;
831  }
832 
833  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyValueName, ValueName );
834  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyPath, L"Control Panel\\Desktop" );
835  InitializeObjectAttributes( &ObjectAttributes,
836  &KeyPath,
837  (OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE | OBJ_FORCE_ACCESS_CHECK),
838  CurrentUserKey,
839  NULL
840  );
841 
842 
843  Status = ExpValidateLocale( MAKELCID( CurrentUserUILanguage, SORT_DEFAULT ) );
844 
845  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
846 
847  Status = ZwOpenKey( &Key,
848  GENERIC_WRITE,
849  &ObjectAttributes
850  );
851  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
852 
853  s = &KeyValueBuffer[ 8 ];
854  *s-- = UNICODE_NULL;
855  i = (ULONG)CurrentUserUILanguage;
856 
857  while (s >= KeyValueBuffer) {
858  Digit = i & 0x0000000F;
859  if (Digit <= 9) {
860  *s-- = (WCHAR)(Digit + L'0');
861  }
862  else {
863  *s-- = (WCHAR)((Digit - 10) + L'A');
864  }
865 
866  i = i >> 4;
867  }
868 
869  Status = ZwSetValueKey( Key,
870  &KeyValueName,
871  0,
872  REG_SZ,
873  KeyValueBuffer,
874  9 * sizeof( WCHAR )
875  );
876  ZwClose( Key );
877  }
878  }
879 
880  ZwClose( CurrentUserKey );
881 
882  return Status;
883 }
884 
885 NTSTATUS
886 ExpGetCurrentUserUILanguage (
887  IN WCHAR *ValueName,
888  OUT LANGID *CurrentUserUILanguageId,
889  IN BOOLEAN bCheckGP
890  )
891 {
892  NTSTATUS Status;
893  OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES ObjectAttributes;
894  UNICODE_STRING KeyPath, KeyValueName, UILanguage;
895  HANDLE CurrentUserKey, Key;
896  WCHAR KeyValueBuffer[ 128 ];
897  PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION KeyValueInformation;
898  ULONG ResultLength;
899  ULONG Digit;
900 
901  PAGED_CODE();
902 
903  KeyValueInformation = (PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION)KeyValueBuffer;
904  Status = RtlOpenCurrentUser( KEY_ENUMERATE_SUB_KEYS, &CurrentUserKey );
905  if (!NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
906  return Status;
907  }
908  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyValueName, ValueName );
909  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyPath, L"Control Panel\\Desktop" );
910  InitializeObjectAttributes( &ObjectAttributes,
911  &KeyPath,
912  (OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE | OBJ_FORCE_ACCESS_CHECK),
913  CurrentUserKey,
914  NULL
915  );
916 
917  //
918  // Let's check if there is a policy installed for the UI language,
919  // and if so, let's use it.
920  //
921  if (!bCheckGP || !NT_SUCCESS( ExpGetUILanguagePolicy( CurrentUserKey, CurrentUserUILanguageId ))) {
922  Status = ZwOpenKey( &Key,
923  GENERIC_READ,
924  &ObjectAttributes
925  );
926  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
927  Status = ZwQueryValueKey( Key,
928  &KeyValueName,
929  KeyValuePartialInformation,
930  KeyValueInformation,
931  sizeof( KeyValueBuffer ),
932  &ResultLength
933  );
934  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
935 
936  if (KeyValueInformation->Type == REG_SZ &&
937  ExpIsValidUILanguage((PWSTR) KeyValueInformation->Data)) {
938 
939  RtlInitUnicodeString( &UILanguage, (PWSTR) KeyValueInformation->Data);
940  Status = RtlUnicodeStringToInteger( &UILanguage,
941  (ULONG) 16,
942  &Digit
943  );
944  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
945  *CurrentUserUILanguageId = (LANGID) Digit;
946  }
947  }
948  else {
949  Status = STATUS_UNSUCCESSFUL;
950  }
951  }
952  ZwClose( Key );
953  }
954  }
955 
956  ZwClose( CurrentUserKey );
957 
958  return Status;
959 }

961 NTSTATUS
962 NtSetDefaultUILanguage (
963  __in LANGID DefaultUILanguageId
964  )
965 {
966  NTSTATUS Status;
967  LANGID LangId;
968 
969  //
970  // if this is called during user logon, then we need to update the user's registry.
971  //
972  if (DefaultUILanguageId == 0) {
973  Status = ExpGetCurrentUserUILanguage( L"MUILanguagePending" ,
974  &LangId,
975  FALSE
976  );
977  if (NT_SUCCESS( Status )) {
978  Status = ExpSetCurrentUserUILanguage( L"MultiUILanguageId" ,
979  LangId
980  );
981  }
982  return Status;
983  }
984 
985  return ExpSetCurrentUserUILanguage( L"MUILanguagePending", DefaultUILanguageId );
986 }

988 NTSTATUS
989 ExpValidateLocale (
990  IN LCID LocaleId
991  )
992 {
993  NTSTATUS Status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER, ReturnStatus;
994  UNICODE_STRING LocaleName, KeyValueName;
995  UNICODE_STRING NlsLocaleKeyPath, NlsSortKeyPath, NlsLangGroupKeyPath;
996  WCHAR LocaleNameBuffer[ 32 ];
997  WCHAR KeyValueNameBuffer[ 32 ];
998  WCHAR KeyValueBuffer[ 128 ];
999  WCHAR *Ptr;
1000  HANDLE LocaleKey, SortKey, LangGroupKey;
1001  OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES NlsLocaleObjA, NlsSortObjA, NlsLangGroupObjA;
1002  PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION KeyValueInformation;
1003  ULONG i, ResultLength;
1004 
1005  //
1006  // Convert the LCID to the form %08x (e.g. 00000409)
1007  //
1008  LocaleName.Length = sizeof( LocaleNameBuffer ) / sizeof( WCHAR );
1009  LocaleName.MaximumLength = LocaleName.Length;
1010  LocaleName.Buffer = LocaleNameBuffer;
1011 
1012  //
1013  // Convert LCID to a string
1014  //
1015  ReturnStatus = RtlIntegerToUnicodeString( LocaleId, 16, &LocaleName );
1016  if (!NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus))
1017  goto Failed1;
1018 
1019  Ptr = KeyValueNameBuffer;
1020  for (i = ((LocaleName.Length)/sizeof(WCHAR));
1021  i < 8;
1022  i++, Ptr++) {
1023  *Ptr = L'0';
1024  }
1025  *Ptr = UNICODE_NULL;
1026 
1027  RtlInitUnicodeString(&KeyValueName, KeyValueNameBuffer);
1028  KeyValueName.MaximumLength = sizeof( KeyValueNameBuffer ) / sizeof( WCHAR );
1029  RtlAppendUnicodeToString(&KeyValueName, LocaleName.Buffer);
1030 
1031 
1032  //
1033  // Open Registry Keys : Locale, Sort and LanguageGroup
1034  //
1035  RtlInitUnicodeString(&NlsLocaleKeyPath,
1036  L"\\Registry\\Machine\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Nls\\Locale");
1037 
1038  InitializeObjectAttributes( &NlsLocaleObjA,
1039  &NlsLocaleKeyPath,
1040  (OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE),
1041  NULL,
1042  NULL
1043  );
1044 
1045  ReturnStatus = ZwOpenKey( &LocaleKey,
1046  GENERIC_READ,
1047  &NlsLocaleObjA
1048  );
1049  if (!NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus))
1050  goto Failed1;
1051 
1052  RtlInitUnicodeString(&NlsSortKeyPath,
1053  L"\\Registry\\Machine\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Nls\\Locale\\Alternate Sorts");
1054 
1055  InitializeObjectAttributes( &NlsSortObjA,
1056  &NlsSortKeyPath,
1057  (OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE),
1058  NULL,
1059  NULL
1060  );
1061 
1062  ReturnStatus = ZwOpenKey( &SortKey,
1063  GENERIC_READ,
1064  &NlsSortObjA
1065  );
1066  if (!NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus))
1067  goto Failed2;
1068 
1069  RtlInitUnicodeString(&NlsLangGroupKeyPath,
1070  L"\\Registry\\Machine\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Nls\\Language Groups");
1071 
1072  InitializeObjectAttributes( &NlsLangGroupObjA,
1073  &NlsLangGroupKeyPath,
1074  (OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE),
1075  NULL,
1076  NULL
1077  );
1078 
1079 
1080  ReturnStatus = ZwOpenKey( &LangGroupKey,
1081  GENERIC_READ,
1082  &NlsLangGroupObjA
1083  );
1084  if (!NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus))
1085  goto Failed3;
1086 
1087  //
1088  // Validate Locale : Lookup the Locale's Language group, and make sure it is there.
1089  //
1090  KeyValueInformation = (PKEY_VALUE_PARTIAL_INFORMATION) KeyValueBuffer;
1091  ReturnStatus = ZwQueryValueKey( LocaleKey,
1092  &KeyValueName,
1093  KeyValuePartialInformation,
1094  KeyValueInformation,
1095  sizeof( KeyValueBuffer ),
1096  &ResultLength
1097  );
1098 
1099  if (!NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus)) {
1100  ReturnStatus = ZwQueryValueKey( SortKey,
1101  &KeyValueName,
1102  KeyValuePartialInformation,
1103  KeyValueInformation,
1104  sizeof( KeyValueBuffer ),
1105  &ResultLength
1106  );
1107  }
1108 
1109  if ((NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus)) &&
1110  (KeyValueInformation->DataLength > 2)
1111  ) {
1112 
1113  RtlInitUnicodeString( &KeyValueName, (PWSTR) KeyValueInformation->Data );
1114 
1115  ReturnStatus = ZwQueryValueKey( LangGroupKey,
1116  &KeyValueName,
1117  KeyValuePartialInformation,
1118  KeyValueInformation,
1119  sizeof( KeyValueBuffer ),
1120  &ResultLength
1121  );
1122  if ((NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus)) &&
1123  (KeyValueInformation->Type == REG_SZ) &&
1124  (KeyValueInformation->DataLength > 2)
1125  ) {
1126  Ptr = (PWSTR) KeyValueInformation->Data;
1127  if (Ptr[0] == L'1' && Ptr[1] == UNICODE_NULL) {
1128  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1129  }
1130  }
1131  }
1132 
1133  //
1134  // Close opened keys
1135  //
1136 
1137  ZwClose( LangGroupKey );
1138 
1139 Failed3:
1140  ZwClose( SortKey );
1141 
1142 Failed2:
1143  ZwClose( LocaleKey );
1144 
1145 Failed1:
1146 
1147  //
1148  // If an error happens, let's record it.
1149  //
1150  if (!NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus)) {
1151  Status = ReturnStatus;
1152  }
1153 
1154  return Status;
1155 }

1157 NTSTATUS
1158 ExpQueryNumaProcessorMap (
1159  OUT PVOID SystemInformation,
1160  IN ULONG SystemInformationLength,
1161  OUT PULONG ReturnedLength
1162  )
1163 {
1164  PSYSTEM_NUMA_INFORMATION Map;
1165  ULONG Length;
1166  ULONG ReturnCount;
1167 #if !defined(NT_UP)
1168  ULONG i;
1169 #endif
1170 
1171  Map = (PSYSTEM_NUMA_INFORMATION)SystemInformation;
1172 
1173  //
1174  // Must be able to return at least the number of nodes.
1175  //
1176 
1177  if (SystemInformationLength < sizeof(Map->HighestNodeNumber)) {
1178  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1179  }
1180 
1181  Map->HighestNodeNumber = KeNumberNodes - 1;
1182 
1183  //
1184  // Return as many node masks as possible in the SystemInformation
1185  // buffer.
1186  //
1187 
1188  Length = FIELD_OFFSET(SYSTEM_NUMA_INFORMATION,
1189  ActiveProcessorsAffinityMask);
1190 
1191  ReturnCount = (SystemInformationLength - Length) /
1192  sizeof(Map->ActiveProcessorsAffinityMask[0]);
1193 
1194  if (ReturnCount > KeNumberNodes) {
1195  ReturnCount = KeNumberNodes;
1196  }
1197 
1198  if ((Length > SystemInformationLength) ||
1199  (ReturnCount == 0)) {
1200  *ReturnedLength = sizeof(Map->HighestNodeNumber);
1201  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
1202  }
1203 
1204  *ReturnedLength = FIELD_OFFSET(SYSTEM_NUMA_INFORMATION,
1205  ActiveProcessorsAffinityMask[ReturnCount]);
1206 
1207 #if !defined(NT_UP)
1208 
1209  for (i = 0; i < ReturnCount; i++) {
1210  Map->ActiveProcessorsAffinityMask[i] = KeNodeBlock[i]->ProcessorMask;
1211  }
1212 
1213 #else
1214 
1215  if (ReturnCount) {
1216  Map->ActiveProcessorsAffinityMask[0] = 1;
1217  }
1218 
1219 #endif
1220 
1221  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
1222 }
1223 
1224 NTSTATUS
1225 ExpQueryNumaAvailableMemory (
1226  OUT PVOID SystemInformation,
1227  IN ULONG SystemInformationLength,
1228  OUT PULONG ReturnedLength
1229  )
1230 {
1231  PSYSTEM_NUMA_INFORMATION Map;
1232  ULONG Length;
1233  ULONG ReturnCount;
1234 
1235  Map = (PSYSTEM_NUMA_INFORMATION)SystemInformation;
1236 
1237  //
1238  // Must be able to return at least the number of nodes.
1239  //
1240 
1241  if (SystemInformationLength < sizeof(Map->HighestNodeNumber)) {
1242  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1243  }
1244 
1245  Map->HighestNodeNumber = KeNumberNodes - 1;
1246 
1247  //
1248  // Return as many node masks as possible in the SystemInformation
1249  // buffer.
1250  //
1251 
1252  Length = FIELD_OFFSET(SYSTEM_NUMA_INFORMATION,
1253  AvailableMemory);
1254 
1255  ReturnCount = (SystemInformationLength - Length) /
1256  sizeof(Map->AvailableMemory[0]);
1257 
1258  if (ReturnCount > KeNumberNodes) {
1259  ReturnCount = KeNumberNodes;
1260  }
1261 
1262  if ((Length > SystemInformationLength) ||
1263  (ReturnCount == 0)) {
1264  *ReturnedLength = sizeof(Map->HighestNodeNumber);
1265  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
1266  }
1267 
1268  *ReturnedLength = FIELD_OFFSET(SYSTEM_NUMA_INFORMATION,
1269  AvailableMemory[ReturnCount]);
1270 
1271  //
1272  // Return the approximate number of free bytes at this time.
1273  // (It's approximate because no lock is taken and with respect
1274  // to any user mode application its only a sample.
1275  //
1276 
1277 #if !defined(NT_UP)
1278 
1279  if (KeNumberNodes > 1) {
1280 
1281  ULONG i;
1282 
1283  for (i = 0; i < ReturnCount; i++) {
1284  Map->AvailableMemory[i] =
1285  ((ULONGLONG)KeNodeBlock[i]->FreeCount[ZeroedPageList] +
1286  (ULONGLONG)KeNodeBlock[i]->FreeCount[FreePageList])
1287  << PAGE_SHIFT;
1288  }
1289  } else
1290 
1291 #endif
1292 
1293  if (ReturnCount) {
1294  Map->AvailableMemory[0] = ((ULONGLONG)MmAvailablePages) << PAGE_SHIFT;
1295  }
1296 
1297 
1298  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
1299 }

1301 NTSTATUS
1302 ExpGetSystemBasicInformation (
1303  OUT PSYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION BasicInfo
1304  )
1305 {
1306  NTSTATUS NtStatus = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1307 
1308  try {
1309 
1310  BasicInfo->NumberOfProcessors = KeNumberProcessors;
1311  BasicInfo->ActiveProcessorsAffinityMask = (ULONG_PTR)KeActiveProcessors;
1312  BasicInfo->Reserved = 0;
1313  BasicInfo->TimerResolution = KeMaximumIncrement;
1314  BasicInfo->NumberOfPhysicalPages = MmNumberOfPhysicalPages;
1315  BasicInfo->LowestPhysicalPageNumber = (SYSINF_PAGE_COUNT)MmLowestPhysicalPage;
1316  BasicInfo->HighestPhysicalPageNumber = (SYSINF_PAGE_COUNT)MmHighestPhysicalPage;
1317  BasicInfo->PageSize = PAGE_SIZE;
1318  BasicInfo->AllocationGranularity = MM_ALLOCATION_GRANULARITY;
1319  BasicInfo->MinimumUserModeAddress = (ULONG_PTR)MM_LOWEST_USER_ADDRESS;
1320  BasicInfo->MaximumUserModeAddress = (ULONG_PTR)MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS;
1321  }
1322  except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1323  NtStatus = GetExceptionCode();
1324  }
1325 
1326  return NtStatus;
1327 }

1341  ProcessorInformation->Reserved = 0;

1343  }
1344  except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {

1346  }
1347 
1348  return NtStatus;
1349 }

1353 NTSTATUS
1354 ExpGetSystemEmulationBasicInformation (
1355  OUT PSYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION BasicInfo
1356  )
1357 {
1358  NTSTATUS NtStatus = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1359 
1360  try {
1361 
1362  BasicInfo->NumberOfProcessors = min(32, KeNumberProcessors);
1363  BasicInfo->ActiveProcessorsAffinityMask = (ULONG_PTR)
1364  ((KeActiveProcessors & 0xFFFFFFFF) | ((KeActiveProcessors & (((ULONG_PTR)0xFFFFFFFF) << 32) ) >> 32));
1365  BasicInfo->Reserved = 0;
1366  BasicInfo->TimerResolution = KeMaximumIncrement;
1367  BasicInfo->NumberOfPhysicalPages = (MmNumberOfPhysicalPages * (PAGE_SIZE >> PAGE_SHIFT_X86NT));
1368  BasicInfo->LowestPhysicalPageNumber = (SYSINF_PAGE_COUNT)MmLowestPhysicalPage;
1369  BasicInfo->HighestPhysicalPageNumber = (SYSINF_PAGE_COUNT)MmHighestPhysicalPage;
1370  BasicInfo->PageSize = PAGE_SIZE_X86NT;
1371  BasicInfo->AllocationGranularity = MM_ALLOCATION_GRANULARITY;
1372  BasicInfo->MinimumUserModeAddress = 0x00000000000010000UI64;
1373 
1374  //
1375  // NOTE: MmGetMaxWowAddress return the highest usermode address boundary,
1376  // thus we are subtracting one to get the maximum accessible usermode address
1377  //
1378 
1379  BasicInfo->MaximumUserModeAddress = ((ULONG_PTR)MmGetMaxWowAddress () - 1);
1380  }
1381  except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1382  NtStatus = GetExceptionCode();
1383  }
1384 
1385  return NtStatus;
1386 }

1388 #endif
1389 
1390 NTSTATUS
1391 NtQuerySystemInformation (
1392  __in SYSTEM_INFORMATION_CLASS SystemInformationClass,
1393  __out_bcount_opt(SystemInformationLength) PVOID SystemInformation,
1394  __in ULONG SystemInformationLength,
1395  __out_opt PULONG ReturnLength
1396  )
1397 
1398 /*++
1399 
1400 Routine Description:
1401 
1402  This function queries information about the system.
1403 
1404 Arguments:
1405 
1406  SystemInformationClass - The system information class about which
1407  to retrieve information.
1408 
1409  SystemInformation - A pointer to a buffer which receives the specified
1410  information. The format and content of the buffer depend on the
1411  specified system information class.
1412 
1413  SystemInformation Format by Information Class:
1414 
1415  SystemBasicInformation - Data type is SYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION
1416 
1417  SYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION Structure
1418 
1419  ULONG Reserved - Always zero.
1420 
1421  ULONG TimerResolutionInMicroSeconds - The resolution of
1422  the hardware time. All time values in NT are
1423  specified as 64-bit LARGE_INTEGER values in units of
1424  100 nanoseconds. This field allows an application to
1425  understand how many of the low order bits of a system
1426  time value are insignificant.
1427 
1428  ULONG PageSize - The physical page size for virtual memory
1429  objects. Physical memory is committed in PageSize
1430  chunks.
1431 
1432  ULONG AllocationGranularity - The logical page size for
1433  virtual memory objects. Allocating 1 byte of virtual
1434  memory will actually allocate AllocationGranularity
1435  bytes of virtual memory. Storing into that byte will
1436  commit the first physical page of the virtual memory.
1437 
1438  ULONG MinimumUserModeAddress - The smallest valid user mode
1439  address. The first AllocationGranularity bytes of
1440  the virtual address space are reserved. This forces
1441  access violations for code the dereferences a zero
1442  pointer.
1443 
1444  ULONG MaximumUserModeAddress - The largest valid user mode
1445  address. The next AllocationGranularity bytes of
1446  the virtual address space are reserved. This allows
1447  system service routines to validate user mode pointer
1448  parameters quickly.
1449 
1450  KAFFINITY ActiveProcessorsAffinityMask - The affinity mask
1451  for the current hardware configuration.
1452 
1453  CCHAR NumberOfProcessors - The number of processors
1454  in the current hardware configuration.
1455 
1456  SystemProcessorInformation - Data type is SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_INFORMATION
1457 
1458  SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_INFORMATION Structure
1459 
1460  USHORT ProcessorArchitecture - The processor architecture:
1461  PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_INTEL
1462  PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_IA64
1463  PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_MIPS
1464  PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_ALPHA
1465  PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_PPC
1466 
1467  USHORT ProcessorLevel - architecture dependent processor level.
1468  This is the least common denominator for an MP system:
1469 
1470  For PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_INTEL:
1471  3 - 386
1472  4 - 486
1473  5 - 586 or Pentium
1474 
1475  For PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_IA64:
1476  7 - Itanium
1477  31 - Itanium 2
1478 
1479  For PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_MIPS:
1480  00xx - where xx is 8-bit implementation number (bits 8-15 of
1481  PRId register.
1482  0004 - R4000
1483 
1484  For PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_ALPHA:
1485  xxxx - where xxxx is 16-bit processor version number (low
1486  order 16 bits of processor version number from firmware)
1487 
1488  21064 - 21064
1489  21066 - 21066
1490  21164 - 21164
1491 
1492  For PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_PPC:
1493  xxxx - where xxxx is 16-bit processor version number (high
1494  order 16 bits of Processor Version Register).
1495  1 - 601
1496  3 - 603
1497  4 - 604
1498  6 - 603+
1499  9 - 604+
1500  20 - 620
1501 
1502  USHORT ProcessorRevision - architecture dependent processor revision.
1503  This is the least common denominator for an MP system:
1504 
1505  For PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_INTEL:
1506  For Old Intel 386 or 486:
1507  FFxx - where xx is displayed as a hexadecimal CPU stepping
1508  (e.g. FFD0 is D0 stepping)
1509 
1510  For Intel Pentium or Cyrix/NexGen 486
1511  xxyy - where xx is model number and yy is stepping, so
1512  0201 is Model 2, Stepping 1
1513 
1514  For PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_IA64:
1515  xxyy - where xx is model number and yy is stepping, so
1516  0201 is Model 2, Stepping 1
1517 
1518  For PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_MIPS:
1519  00xx is 8-bit revision number of processor (low order 8 bits
1520  of PRId Register
1521 
1522  For PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_ALPHA:
1523  xxyy - where xxyy is 16-bit processor revision number (low
1524  order 16 bits of processor revision number from firmware).
1525  Displayed as Model 'A'+xx, Pass yy
1526 
1527  For PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_PPC:
1528  xxyy - where xxyy is 16-bit processor revision number (low
1529  order 16 bits of Processor Version Register). Displayed
1530  as a fixed point number xx.yy
1531 
1532  USHORT Reserved - Always zero.
1533 
1534  ULONG ProcessorFeatureBits - architecture dependent processor feature bits.
1535  This is the least common denominator for an MP system.
1536 
1537  SystemPerformanceInformation - Data type is SYSTEM_PERFORMANCE_INFORMATION
1538 
1539  SYSTEM_PERFORMANCE_INFORMATION Structure
1540 
1541  LARGE_INTEGER IdleProcessTime - Returns the kernel time of the idle
1542  process.
1543 
1544  LARGE_INTEGER IoReadTransferCount;
1545  LARGE_INTEGER IoWriteTransferCount;
1546  LARGE_INTEGER IoOtherTransferCount;
1547  LARGE_INTEGER KernelTime;
1548  LARGE_INTEGER UserTime;
1549  ULONG IoReadOperationCount;
1550  ULONG IoWriteOperationCount;
1551  ULONG IoOtherOperationCount;
1552  ULONG AvailablePages;
1553  ULONG CommittedPages;
1554  ULONG PageFaultCount;
1555  ULONG CopyOnWriteCount;
1556  ULONG TransitionCount;
1557  ULONG CacheTransitionCount;
1558  ULONG DemandZeroCount;
1559  ULONG PageReadCount;
1560  ULONG PageReadIoCount;
1561  ULONG CacheReadCount;
1562  ULONG CacheIoCount;
1563  ULONG DirtyPagesWriteCount;
1564  ULONG DirtyWriteIoCount;
1565  ULONG MappedPagesWriteCount;
1566  ULONG MappedWriteIoCount;
1567  ULONG PagedPoolPages;
1568  ULONG NonPagedPoolPages;
1569  ULONG PagedPoolAllocs;
1570  ULONG PagedPoolFrees;
1571  ULONG NonPagedPoolAllocs;
1572  ULONG NonPagedPoolFrees;
1573  ULONG LpcThreadsWaitingInReceive;
1574  ULONG LpcThreadsWaitingForReply;
1575 
1576  SystemProcessInformation - Data type is SYSTEM_PROCESS_INFORMATION
1577 
1578  SYSTEM_PROCESS_INFORMATION Structure
1579 
1580  SystemDockInformation - Data type is SYSTEM_DOCK_INFORMATION
1581 
1582  SYSTEM_DOCK_INFORMATION Structure
1583 
1584  SYSTEM_DOCKED_STATE DockState - Ordinal specifying the current docking state. Possible values:
1585  SystemDockStateUnknown - The docking state of the system could not be determined.
1586  SystemUndocked - The system is undocked.
1587  SystemDocked - The system is docked.
1588 
1589  ULONG DockIdLength - Specifies the length in characters of the Dock ID string
1590  (not including terminating NULL).
1591 
1592  ULONG SerialNumberOffset - Specifies the character offset of the Serial Number within
1593  the DockId buffer.
1594 
1595  ULONG SerialNumberLength - Specifies the length in characters of the Serial Number
1596  string (not including terminating NULL).
1597 
1598  WCHAR DockId - Character buffer containing two null-terminated strings. The first
1599  string is a character representation of the dock ID number, starting
1600  at the beginning of the buffer. The second string is a character
1601  representation of the machine's serial number, starting at character
1602  offset SerialNumberOffset in the buffer.
1603 
1604 
1605  SystemPowerSettings - Data type is SYSTEM_POWER_SETTINGS
1606  SYSTEM_POWER_INFORMATION Structure
1607  BOOLEAN SystemSuspendSupported - Supplies a BOOLEAN as to
1608  whether the system suspend is enabled or not.
1609  BOOLEAN SystemHibernateSupported - Supplies a BOOLEAN as to
1610  whether the system hibernate is enabled or not.
1611  BOOLEAN ResumeTimerSupportsSuspend - Supplies a BOOLEAN as to
1612  whether the resuming from an external programmed timer
1613  from within a system suspend is enabled or not.
1614  BOOLEAN ResumeTimerSupportsHibernate - Supplies a BOOLEAN as to
1615  whether or resuming from an external programmed timer
1616  from within a system hibernate is enabled or not.
1617  BOOLEAN LidSupported - Supplies a BOOLEAN as to whether or not
1618  the suspending and resuming by Lid are enabled or not.
1619  BOOLEAN TurboSettingSupported - Supplies a BOOLEAN as to whether
1620  or not the system supports a turbo mode setting.
1621  BOOLEAN TurboMode - Supplies a BOOLEAN as to whether or not
1622  the system is in turbo mode.
1623  BOOLEAN SystemAcOrDc - Supplies a BOOLEAN as to whether or not
1624  the system is in AC mode.
1625  BOOLEAN DisablePowerDown - If TRUE, signifies that all requests to
1626  PoRequestPowerChange for a SET_POWER-PowerDown irp are to
1627  be ignored.
1628  LARGE_INTEGER SpindownDrives - If non-zero, signifies to the
1629  cache manager (or the IO subsystem) to optimize drive
1630  accesses based upon power saves, are that drives are to
1631  be spun down as appropriate. The value represents to user's
1632  requested disk spin down timeout.
1633 
1634  SystemProcessorSpeedInformation - Data type is SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_SPEED_INFORMATION
1635  SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_SPEED_INFORMATION Structure (same as HalProcessorSpeedInformation)
1636  ULONG MaximumProcessorSpeed - The maximum hertz the processor is
1637  capable of. This information is used by the UI to draw the
1638  appropriate scale. This field is read-only and cannot be
1639  set.
1640  ULONG CurrentAvailableSpeed - The hertz for which the processor
1641  runs at when not idle. This field is read-only and cannot
1642  be set.
1643  ULONG ConfiguredSpeedLimit - The hertz for which the processor
1644  is limited to due to the current configuration.
1645  UCHAR PowerState
1646  0 - Normal
1647  1 - The processor speed is being limited due to available
1648  power restrictions. This field id read-only by the system.
1649  UCHAR ThermalState
1650  0 - Normal
1651  1 - The processors speed is being limited due to thermal
1652  restrictions. This field is read-only by the system.
1653  UCHAR TurboState
1654  0 - Normal
1655  1 - The processors speed is being limited by the fact that
1656  the system turbo mode is currently disabled which is
1657  requested to obtain more processor speed.
1658 
1659  SystemInformationLength - Specifies the length in bytes of the system
1660  information buffer.
1661 
1662  ReturnLength - An optional pointer which, if specified, receives the
1663  number of bytes placed in the system information buffer.
1664 
1665 Return Value:
1666 
1667  Returns one of the following status codes:
1668 
1669  STATUS_SUCCESS - normal, successful completion.
1670 
1671  STATUS_INVALID_INFO_CLASS - The SystemInformationClass parameter
1672  did not specify a valid value.
1673 
1674  STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH - The value of the SystemInformationLength
1675  parameter did not match the length required for the information
1676  class requested by the SystemInformationClass parameter.
1677 
1678  STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION - Either the SystemInformation buffer pointer
1679  or the ReturnLength pointer value specified an invalid address.
1680 
1681  STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA - The process does not have sufficient
1682  working set to lock the specified output structure in memory.
1683 
1684  STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES - Insufficient system resources exist
1685  for this request to complete.
1686 
1687 --*/

1689 {
1690

1722  PAGED_CODE();

1725  // Assume successful completion.
1726  //

1728  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1729  try {
1730 
1731  //
1732  // Get previous processor mode and probe output argument if necessary.
1733  //
1734 
1735  PreviousMode = KeGetPreviousMode();
1736  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
1737 
1738  Alignment = sizeof(ULONG);
1739 
1740  if (SystemInformationClass == SystemKernelDebuggerInformation) {
1741  Alignment = sizeof(BOOLEAN);
1742  } else if (SystemInformationClass == SystemLocksInformation) {
1743  Alignment = sizeof(PVOID);
1744  }
1745 
1746  ProbeForWrite(SystemInformation,
1747  SystemInformationLength,
1748  Alignment);
1749 
1750  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(ReturnLength)) {
1751  ProbeForWriteUlong(ReturnLength);
1752  }
1753  }
1754 
1755  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(ReturnLength)) {
1756  *ReturnLength = 0;
1757  }

1760 
1761  case SystemBasicInformation:
1762 
1763  if (SystemInformationLength != sizeof( SYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION )) {
1764  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1765  }
1766 
1767  Status = ExpGetSystemBasicInformation ((PSYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION)SystemInformation);
1768 
1769  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status) && ARGUMENT_PRESENT( ReturnLength )) {
1770  *ReturnLength = sizeof( SYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION );
1771  }
1772  break;
1773 
1774  case SystemEmulationBasicInformation:
1775 
1776  if (SystemInformationLength != sizeof( SYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION )) {
1777  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1778  }
1779 
1780 #if defined(_WIN64)
1781  Status = ExpGetSystemEmulationBasicInformation ((PSYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION)SystemInformation);
1782 #else
1783  Status = ExpGetSystemBasicInformation ((PSYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION)SystemInformation);
1784 #endif
1785 
1786  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status) && ARGUMENT_PRESENT( ReturnLength )) {
1787  *ReturnLength = sizeof( SYSTEM_BASIC_INFORMATION );
1788  }
1789  break;
1790 
1791  case SystemProcessorInformation:
1792  if (SystemInformationLength < sizeof( SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_INFORMATION )) {
1793  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1794  }
1795 
1796  Status = ExpGetSystemProcessorInformation ((PSYSTEM_PROCESSOR_INFORMATION)SystemInformation);
1797 
1798  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status) && ARGUMENT_PRESENT( ReturnLength )) {
1799  *ReturnLength = sizeof( SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_INFORMATION );
1800  }
1801 
1802  break;
1803 
1804  case SystemEmulationProcessorInformation:
1805 
1806  if (SystemInformationLength < sizeof( SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_INFORMATION )) {
1807  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1808  }
1809 
1810 #if defined(_WIN64)
1811  Status = ExpGetSystemEmulationProcessorInformation ((PSYSTEM_PROCESSOR_INFORMATION)SystemInformation);
1812 #else
1813  Status = ExpGetSystemProcessorInformation ((PSYSTEM_PROCESSOR_INFORMATION)SystemInformation);
1814 #endif
1815 
1816  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status) && ARGUMENT_PRESENT( ReturnLength )) {
1817  *ReturnLength = sizeof( SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_INFORMATION );
1818  }
1819 
1820  break;

1823  if (SystemInformationLength < sizeof( SYSTEM_PERFORMANCE_INFORMATION )) {
1824  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1825  }

1828 
1829  //
1830  // Io information.
1831  //
1832  // These counters are kept on a per processor basis and must
1833  // be totaled.
1834  //
1835 
1836  {
1837 
1838  ULONG OtherOperationCount;
1839  LARGE_INTEGER OtherTransferCount;
1840  ULONG ReadOperationCount;
1841  LARGE_INTEGER ReadTransferCount;
1842  ULONG WriteOperationCount;
1843  LARGE_INTEGER WriteTransferCount;
1844 
1845  OtherOperationCount = IoOtherOperationCount;
1846  OtherTransferCount.QuadPart = IoOtherTransferCount.QuadPart;
1847  ReadOperationCount = IoReadOperationCount;
1848  ReadTransferCount.QuadPart = IoReadTransferCount.QuadPart;
1849  WriteOperationCount = IoWriteOperationCount;
1850  WriteTransferCount.QuadPart = IoWriteTransferCount.QuadPart;
1851  for (i = 0; i < (ULONG)KeNumberProcessors; i += 1) {
1852  Prcb = KiProcessorBlock[i];
1853  if (Prcb != NULL) {
1854  OtherOperationCount += Prcb->IoOtherOperationCount;
1855  OtherTransferCount.QuadPart += Prcb->IoOtherTransferCount.QuadPart;
1856  ReadOperationCount += Prcb->IoReadOperationCount;
1857  ReadTransferCount.QuadPart += Prcb->IoReadTransferCount.QuadPart;
1858  WriteOperationCount += Prcb->IoWriteOperationCount;
1859  WriteTransferCount.QuadPart += Prcb->IoWriteTransferCount.QuadPart;
1860  }
1861  }
1862

1864  LocalPerformanceInfo.IoWriteTransferCount = WriteTransferCount;
1865  LocalPerformanceInfo.IoOtherTransferCount = OtherTransferCount;
1866  LocalPerformanceInfo.IoReadOperationCount = ReadOperationCount;
1867  LocalPerformanceInfo.IoWriteOperationCount = WriteOperationCount;
1868  LocalPerformanceInfo.IoOtherOperationCount = OtherOperationCount;
1869  }
1870

1872  // Ke information.
1873  //
1874  // These counters are kept on a per processor basis and must
1875  // be totaled.
1876  //

1880  ULONG SecondLevelTbFills = 0;
1881  ULONG SystemCalls = 0;
1882 
1883  ContextSwitches = 0;
1884  for (i = 0; i < (ULONG)KeNumberProcessors; i += 1) {
1885  Prcb = KiProcessorBlock[i];
1886  if (Prcb != NULL) {
1887  ContextSwitches += KeGetContextSwitches(Prcb);
1888  FirstLevelTbFills += Prcb->KeFirstLevelTbFills;
1889  SecondLevelTbFills += Prcb->KeSecondLevelTbFills;
1890  SystemCalls += Prcb->KeSystemCalls;
1891  }
1892  }

1895  LocalPerformanceInfo.FirstLevelTbFills = FirstLevelTbFills;
1896  LocalPerformanceInfo.SecondLevelTbFills = SecondLevelTbFills;
1897  LocalPerformanceInfo.SystemCalls = SystemCalls;
1898  }

1904  // must be totaled.
1905  //

1908  LocalPerformanceInfo.CommittedPages = (SYSINF_PAGE_COUNT)MmTotalCommittedPages;
1909  LocalPerformanceInfo.CommitLimit = (SYSINF_PAGE_COUNT)MmTotalCommitLimit;
1910  LocalPerformanceInfo.PeakCommitment = (SYSINF_PAGE_COUNT)MmPeakCommitment;
1911 
1912  {
1913 
1914  ULONG PageFaultCount = 0;
1915  ULONG CopyOnWriteCount = 0;
1916  ULONG TransitionCount = 0;
1917  ULONG CacheTransitionCount = 0;
1918  ULONG DemandZeroCount = 0;

1922  ULONG CacheIoCount = 0;

1926  ULONG MappedWriteIoCount = 0;

1930  if (Prcb != NULL) {
1931  PageFaultCount += Prcb->MmPageFaultCount;
1932  CopyOnWriteCount += Prcb->MmCopyOnWriteCount;
1933  TransitionCount += Prcb->MmTransitionCount;
1934  CacheTransitionCount += Prcb->MmCacheTransitionCount;
1935  DemandZeroCount += Prcb->MmDemandZeroCount;
1936  PageReadCount += Prcb->MmPageReadCount;
1937  PageReadIoCount += Prcb->MmPageReadIoCount;
1938  CacheReadCount += Prcb->MmCacheReadCount;
1939  CacheIoCount += Prcb->MmCacheIoCount;
1940  DirtyPagesWriteCount += Prcb->MmDirtyPagesWriteCount;
1941  DirtyWriteIoCount += Prcb->MmDirtyWriteIoCount;
1942  MappedPagesWriteCount += Prcb->MmMappedPagesWriteCount;
1943  MappedWriteIoCount += Prcb->MmMappedWriteIoCount;
1944  }

1953  LocalPerformanceInfo.PageReadIoCount = PageReadIoCount;
1954  LocalPerformanceInfo.CacheReadCount = CacheReadCount;
1955  LocalPerformanceInfo.CacheIoCount = CacheIoCount;

1957  LocalPerformanceInfo.DirtyWriteIoCount = DirtyWriteIoCount;

3066 NTSTATUS

3074 /*++
3075 
3076 Routine Description:
3077 
3078  This function set information about the system.
3079 
3080 Arguments:
3081

3083  be modified.

3091  information buffer.

3094

3096

3098

3100  is not accessible.
3101 
3102  STATUS_INVALID_INFO_CLASS - The SystemInformationClass parameter
3103  did not specify a valid value.
3104 
3105  STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH - The value of the SystemInformationLength
3106  parameter did not match the length required for the information
3107  class requested by the SystemInformationClass parameter.

3700  KiIdealDpcRate = DpcInfo.IdealDpcRate;
3701  }

3703 
3704  case SystemSessionCreate:
3705  {
3706 
3707  //
3708  // Creation of a session space.
3709  //
3710 
3711  ULONG SessionId;
3712 
3713  //

3715  // then return an error.
3716  //
3717 
3718  if (SystemInformationLength != sizeof(ULONG)) {
3719  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
3720  }
3721

3723

3726  // ensure that the caller has the privilege to load
3727  // a driver.
3728  //
3729 
3730  if (!SeSinglePrivilegeCheck (SeLoadDriverPrivilege, PreviousMode)) {
3731  return STATUS_PRIVILEGE_NOT_HELD;

3735  ProbeForWriteUlong((PULONG)SystemInformation);

3738  return GetExceptionCode();
3739  }
3740  }

3743  // Create a session space in the current process.
3744  //
3745

3747

3749  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
3750  try {
3751  *(PULONG)SystemInformation = SessionId;
3752  }
3753  except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
3754  return GetExceptionCode();
3755  }
3756  }
3757  else {
3758  *(PULONG)SystemInformation = SessionId;
3759  }
3760  }
3761

3763  }

3772  // then return an error.
3773  //

3780

3783  // ensure that the caller has the privilege to load
3784  // a driver.
3785  //

3787  if (!SeSinglePrivilegeCheck( SeLoadDriverPrivilege, PreviousMode )) {
3788  return STATUS_PRIVILEGE_NOT_HELD;

4122 
4123 NTSTATUS
4124 ExLockUserBuffer (
4125  __inout_bcount(Length) PVOID Buffer,
4126  __in ULONG Length,
4127  __in KPROCESSOR_MODE ProbeMode,
4128  __in LOCK_OPERATION LockMode,
4129  __deref_out PVOID *LockedBuffer,
4130  __deref_out PVOID *LockVariable
4131  )
4132 
4133 /*++
4134 
4135 Routine Description:
4136 
4137  Wrapper for MmProbeAndLockPages. Creates an MDL and locks the
4138  specified buffer with that MDL.
4139 
4140 Arguments:
4141 
4142  Buffer - pointer to the buffer to be locked.
4143  Length - size of the buffer to be locked.
4144  ProbeMode - processor mode for doing the probe in MmProbeAndLockPages.
4145  LockMode - the mode the pages should be locked for.
4146  LockedBuffer - returns a pointer to the locked buffer for use by the
4147  caller.
4148  LockVariable - returns a context pointer. This must be passed into
4149  ExUnlockUserBuffer when complete so the MDL can be freed.
4150 
4151 Return Value:
4152 
4153  Returns one of the following status codes:
4154 
4155  STATUS_SUCCESS - Normal, successful completion.
4156 
4157  STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION - The buffer is not accessible with the
4158  specified LockMode.
4159 
4160  STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES - not enough memory to allocate the MDL.
4161 
4162 
4163 --*/
4164 
4165 {
4166  PMDL Mdl;
4167  SIZE_T MdlSize;
4168 
4169  //
4170  // It is the caller's responsibility to ensure zero cannot be passed in.
4171  //
4172 
4173  ASSERT (Length != 0);
4174 
4175  *LockedBuffer = NULL;
4176  *LockVariable = NULL;
4177 
4178  //
4179  // Allocate an MDL to map the request.
4180  //
4181 
4182  MdlSize = MmSizeOfMdl( Buffer, Length );
4183  Mdl = ExAllocatePoolWithQuotaTag (NonPagedPool | POOL_QUOTA_FAIL_INSTEAD_OF_RAISE,
4184  MdlSize,
4185  'ofnI');
4186  if (Mdl == NULL) {
4187  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4188  }
4189 
4190  //
4191  // Initialize MDL for request.
4192  //
4193 
4194  MmInitializeMdl(Mdl, Buffer, Length);
4195 
4196  try {
4197 
4198  MmProbeAndLockPages (Mdl, ProbeMode, LockMode);
4199 
4200  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
4201 
4202  ExFreePool (Mdl);
4203 
4204  return GetExceptionCode();
4205  }
4206 
4207  Mdl->MdlFlags |= MDL_MAPPING_CAN_FAIL;
4208  *LockedBuffer = MmGetSystemAddressForMdl (Mdl);
4209  if (*LockedBuffer == NULL) {
4210  ExUnlockUserBuffer (Mdl);
4211  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4212  }
4213 
4214  *LockVariable = Mdl;
4215  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
4216 }
4217 
4218 VOID
4219 ExUnlockUserBuffer (
4220  __inout PVOID LockVariable
4221  )
4222 
4223 {
4224  MmUnlockPages ((PMDL)LockVariable);
4225  ExFreePool ((PMDL)LockVariable);
4226  return;
4227 }
4228 
4229 NTSTATUS
4230 ExpGetProcessInformation (
4231  OUT PVOID SystemInformation,
4232  IN ULONG SystemInformationLength,
4233  OUT PULONG Length OPTIONAL,
4234  IN PULONG SessionId OPTIONAL,
4235  IN BOOLEAN ExtendedInformation
4236  )
4237 
4238 /*++
4239 
4240 Routine Description:
4241 
4242  This function returns information about all the processes and
4243  threads in the system.
4244 
4245 Arguments:
4246 
4247  SystemInformation - A pointer to a buffer which receives the specified
4248  information.
4249 
4250  SystemInformationLength - Specifies the length in bytes of the system
4251  information buffer.
4252 
4253  Length - An optional pointer which, if specified, receives the
4254  number of bytes placed in the system information buffer.
4255 
4256  SessionId - Session Id.
4257 
4258  ExtendedInformation - TRUE if extended information (e.g., Process PDE) is needed.
4259 
4260 Environment:
4261 
4262  Kernel mode.
4263 
4264  This routine could be made PAGELK but it is a high frequency routine
4265  so it is actually better to keep it nonpaged to avoid bringing in the
4266  entire PAGELK section.
4267 
4268 Return Value:
4269 
4270  Returns one of the following status codes:
4271 
4272  STATUS_SUCCESS - normal, successful completion.
4273 
4274  STATUS_INVALID_INFO_CLASS - The SystemInformationClass parameter
4275  did not specify a valid value.
4276 
4277  STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH - The value of the SystemInformationLength
4278  parameter did not match the length required for the information
4279  class requested by the SystemInformationClass parameter.
4280 
4281  STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION - Either the SystemInformation buffer pointer
4282  or the Length pointer value specified an invalid address.
4283 
4284  STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA - The process does not have sufficient
4285  working set to lock the specified output structure in memory.
4286 
4287  STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES - Insufficient system resources exist
4288  for this request to complete.
4289 
4290 --*/
4291 
4292 {
4293  KLOCK_QUEUE_HANDLE LockHandle;
4294  PEPROCESS Process = NULL;
4295  PETHREAD Thread;
4296  PSYSTEM_PROCESS_INFORMATION ProcessInfo;
4297  PVOID ThreadInfo;
4298  ULONG ThreadInfoSize;
4299  PLIST_ENTRY NextThread;
4300  PVOID MappedAddress;
4301  PVOID LockVariable;
4302  ULONG ProcessSessionId;
4303  ULONG TotalSize = 0;
4304  ULONG NextEntryOffset = 0;
4305  PUCHAR Src;
4306  PWCHAR SrcW;
4307  PWSTR Dst;
4308  ULONG n, nc;
4309  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_SUCCESS, status1;
4310  PUNICODE_STRING pImageFileName;
4311 
4312  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(Length)) {
4313  *Length = 0;
4314  }
4315 
4316  if (SystemInformationLength > 0) {
4317  status1 = ExLockUserBuffer (SystemInformation,
4318  SystemInformationLength,
4319  KeGetPreviousMode(),
4320  IoWriteAccess,
4321  &MappedAddress,
4322  &LockVariable);
4323 
4324  if (!NT_SUCCESS(status1)) {
4325  return status1;
4326  }
4327 
4328  } else {
4329 
4330  //
4331  // This indicates the caller just wants to know the size of the
4332  // buffer to allocate but is not prepared to accept any data content
4333  // in this instance.
4334  //
4335 
4336  MappedAddress = NULL;
4337  LockVariable = NULL;
4338  }
4339 
4340  if (ExtendedInformation) {
4341  ThreadInfoSize = sizeof(SYSTEM_EXTENDED_THREAD_INFORMATION);
4342 
4343  } else {
4344  ThreadInfoSize = sizeof(SYSTEM_THREAD_INFORMATION);
4345  }
4346 
4347  ProcessInfo = (PSYSTEM_PROCESS_INFORMATION) MappedAddress;
4348 
4349  try {
4350 
4351  //
4352  // Do the idle process first then all the other processes.
4353  //
4354 
4355  for (Process = PsIdleProcess;
4356  Process != NULL;
4357  Process = PsGetNextProcess ((Process == PsIdleProcess) ? NULL : Process)) {
4358 
4359  //
4360  // If the process is marked as exiting, the executive process has
4361  // no active threads, the kernel process has no threads, and the
4362  // kernel process has been signaled, then skip the process.
4363  //
4364  // N.B. It is safe to examine the kernel thread list without a
4365  // lock since no list pointers are dereferenced.
4366  //
4367 
4368  if (((Process->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_PROCESS_EXITING) != 0) &&
4369  (Process->Pcb.Header.SignalState != 0) &&
4370  (Process->ActiveThreads == 0) &&
4371  (IsListEmpty(&Process->Pcb.ThreadListHead) == TRUE)) {
4372 
4373  continue;
4374  }
4375 
4376  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(SessionId) && (Process == PsIdleProcess)) {
4377  continue;
4378  }
4379 
4380  ProcessSessionId = MmGetSessionId (Process);
4381  if ((ARGUMENT_PRESENT(SessionId)) &&
4382  (ProcessSessionId != *SessionId)) {
4383  continue;
4384  }
4385 
4386  ProcessInfo = (PSYSTEM_PROCESS_INFORMATION)
4387  ((PUCHAR)MappedAddress + TotalSize);
4388 
4389  NextEntryOffset = sizeof(SYSTEM_PROCESS_INFORMATION);
4390  TotalSize += sizeof(SYSTEM_PROCESS_INFORMATION);
4391  if (TotalSize > SystemInformationLength) {
4392  status = STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
4393  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(Length) == FALSE) {
4394  leave;
4395  }
4396 
4397  } else {
4398 
4399  //
4400  // Get information for each process.
4401  //
4402 
4403  ExpCopyProcessInfo (ProcessInfo, Process, ExtendedInformation);
4404  ProcessInfo->NumberOfThreads = 0;
4405  ProcessInfo->NextEntryOffset = 0;
4406 
4407  //
4408  // Store the Remote Terminal SessionId
4409  //
4410 
4411  ProcessInfo->SessionId = ProcessSessionId;
4412  ProcessInfo->ImageName.Buffer = NULL;
4413  ProcessInfo->ImageName.Length = 0;
4414  ProcessInfo->ImageName.MaximumLength = 0;
4415  if (Process == PsIdleProcess) {
4416 
4417  //
4418  // Since Idle process and system process share the same
4419  // object table, zero out idle processes handle count to
4420  // reduce confusion
4421  //
4422  // Idle Process always has SessionId 0
4423  //
4424 
4425  ProcessInfo->HandleCount = 0;
4426  ProcessInfo->SessionId = 0;
4427  }
4428  }
4429 
4430  //
4431  // Raise IRQL to SYNCH_LEVEL, acquire the kernel process lock, and
4432  // get information for each thread.
4433  //
4434 
4435  ThreadInfo = (PVOID)(ProcessInfo + 1);
4436  KeAcquireInStackQueuedSpinLockRaiseToSynch(&Process->Pcb.ProcessLock,
4437  &LockHandle);
4438 
4439  NextThread = Process->Pcb.ThreadListHead.Flink;
4440  while (NextThread != &Process->Pcb.ThreadListHead) {
4441  NextEntryOffset += ThreadInfoSize;
4442  TotalSize += ThreadInfoSize;
4443 
4444  if (TotalSize > SystemInformationLength) {
4445  status = STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
4446  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(Length) == FALSE) {
4447  KeReleaseInStackQueuedSpinLock(&LockHandle);
4448  leave;
4449  }
4450 
4451  } else {
4452  Thread = (PETHREAD)(CONTAINING_RECORD(NextThread,
4453  KTHREAD,
4454  ThreadListEntry));
4455 
4456  //
4457  // Lock dispatcher database to get atomic view of thread
4458  // attributes.
4459  //
4460 
4461  KiLockDispatcherDatabaseAtSynchLevel();
4462  ExpCopyThreadInfo (ThreadInfo, Thread, ExtendedInformation);
4463  KiUnlockDispatcherDatabaseFromSynchLevel();
4464  ProcessInfo->NumberOfThreads += 1;
4465  ThreadInfo = (PCHAR) ThreadInfo + ThreadInfoSize;
4466  }
4467 
4468  NextThread = NextThread->Flink;
4469  }
4470 
4471  //
4472  // Unlock kernel process lock and lower IRQL to its previous value.
4473  //
4474 
4475  KeReleaseInStackQueuedSpinLock(&LockHandle);
4476 
4477  //
4478  // Get the image name.
4479  //
4480 
4481  if (Process != PsIdleProcess) {
4482 
4483  //
4484  // Try to use the real image name if we can that not limited to 16 characters
4485  //
4486 
4487  Dst = (PWSTR)(ThreadInfo);
4488  status1 = SeLocateProcessImageName (Process, &pImageFileName);
4489  if (NT_SUCCESS (status1)) {
4490  n = pImageFileName->Length;
4491  if (n == 0) {
4492  ExFreePool (pImageFileName);
4493  }
4494 
4495  } else {
4496  n = 0;
4497  }
4498 
4499  if (n) {
4500  SrcW = pImageFileName->Buffer + n / sizeof (WCHAR);
4501  while (SrcW != pImageFileName->Buffer) {
4502  if (*--SrcW == L'\\') {
4503  SrcW = SrcW + 1;
4504  break;
4505  }
4506  }
4507 
4508  nc = n - (ULONG)(SrcW - pImageFileName->Buffer) * sizeof (WCHAR);
4509  n = ROUND_UP (nc + 1, sizeof(LARGE_INTEGER));
4510  TotalSize += n;
4511  NextEntryOffset += n;
4512  if (TotalSize > SystemInformationLength) {
4513  status = STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
4514  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(Length) == FALSE) {
4515  ExFreePool (pImageFileName);
4516  leave;
4517  }
4518  } else {
4519  RtlCopyMemory (Dst, SrcW, nc);
4520  Dst += nc / sizeof (WCHAR);
4521  *Dst++ = L'\0';
4522  }
4523 
4524  ExFreePool (pImageFileName);
4525 
4526  } else {
4527  Src = Process->ImageFileName;
4528  n = (ULONG) strlen ((PCHAR)Src);
4529  if (n != 0) {
4530  n = ROUND_UP( ((n + 1) * sizeof( WCHAR )), sizeof(LARGE_INTEGER) );
4531  TotalSize += n;
4532  NextEntryOffset += n;
4533  if (TotalSize > SystemInformationLength) {
4534  status = STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
4535  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(Length) == FALSE) {
4536  leave;
4537  }
4538 
4539  } else {
4540  WCHAR c;
4541 
4542  while (1) {
4543  c = (WCHAR)*Src++;
4544  *Dst++ = c;
4545  if (c == L'\0') {
4546  break;
4547  }
4548  }
4549  }
4550  }
4551  }
4552 
4553  if (NT_SUCCESS (status)) {
4554  ProcessInfo->ImageName.Length = (USHORT)((PCHAR)Dst -
4555  (PCHAR)ThreadInfo - sizeof( UNICODE_NULL ));
4556 
4557  ProcessInfo->ImageName.MaximumLength = (USHORT)n;
4558 
4559  //
4560  // Set the image name to point into the user's memory.
4561  //
4562 
4563  ProcessInfo->ImageName.Buffer = (PWSTR)
4564  ((PCHAR)SystemInformation +
4565  ((PCHAR)(ThreadInfo) - (PCHAR)MappedAddress));
4566  }
4567  }
4568 
4569  //
4570  // Point to next process.
4571  //
4572 
4573  if (NT_SUCCESS (status)) {
4574  ProcessInfo->NextEntryOffset = NextEntryOffset;
4575  }
4576  }
4577 
4578  if (NT_SUCCESS(status)) {
4579  ProcessInfo->NextEntryOffset = 0;
4580  }
4581 
4582  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(Length)) {
4583  *Length = TotalSize;
4584  }
4585 
4586  } finally {
4587 
4588  if ((Process != NULL) && (Process != PsIdleProcess)) {
4589  PsQuitNextProcess (Process);
4590  }
4591 
4592  if (MappedAddress != NULL) {
4593  ExUnlockUserBuffer (LockVariable);
4594  }
4595  }
4596 
4597  return status;
4598 }
4599 
4600 NTSTATUS
4601 ExGetSessionPoolTagInformation (
4602  OUT PVOID SystemInformation,
4603  IN ULONG SystemInformationLength,
4604  OUT PULONG Length,
4605  IN PULONG SessionId OPTIONAL
4606  )
4607 
4608 /*++
4609 
4610 Routine Description:
4611 
4612  This function returns information about all the per-session pool tag
4613  information in the system.
4614 
4615 Arguments:
4616 
4617  SystemInformation - A pointer to a buffer which receives the specified
4618  information.
4619 
4620  SystemInformationLength - Specifies the length in bytes of the system
4621  information buffer.
4622 
4623  Length - Receives the number of bytes placed (or would have been placed)
4624  in the system information buffer.
4625 
4626  SessionId - Session Id (-1 indicates enumerate all sessions).
4627 
4628 Environment:
4629 
4630  Kernel mode.
4631 
4632 Return Value:
4633 
4634  Returns one of the following status codes:
4635 
4636  STATUS_SUCCESS - normal, successful completion.
4637 
4638  STATUS_INVALID_INFO_CLASS - The SystemInformationClass parameter
4639  did not specify a valid value.
4640 
4641  STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH - The value of the SystemInformationLength
4642  parameter did not match the length required for the information
4643  class requested by the SystemInformationClass parameter.
4644 
4645  STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION - Either the SystemInformation buffer pointer
4646  or the Length pointer value specified an invalid address.
4647 
4648  STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA - The process does not have sufficient
4649  working set to lock the specified output structure in memory.
4650 
4651  STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES - Insufficient system resources exist
4652  for this request to complete.
4653 
4654 --*/
4655 
4656 {
4657  KAPC_STATE ApcState;
4658  PVOID MappedAddress;
4659  PVOID OpaqueSession;
4660  PVOID LockVariable;
4661  ULONG TotalSize;
4662  ULONG NextEntryOffset;
4663  ULONG CurrentSessionId;
4664  ULONG Count;
4665  ULONG AbsoluteCount;
4666  NTSTATUS status;
4667  NTSTATUS status1;
4668  PSYSTEM_SESSION_POOLTAG_INFORMATION SessionPoolTagInfo;
4669 
4670  *Length = 0;
4671  TotalSize = 0;
4672  NextEntryOffset = 0;
4673  status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
4674  SessionPoolTagInfo = NULL;
4675 
4676  if (SystemInformationLength > 0) {
4677 
4678  status1 = ExLockUserBuffer (SystemInformation,
4679  SystemInformationLength,
4680  KeGetPreviousMode(),
4681  IoWriteAccess,
4682  &MappedAddress,
4683  &LockVariable);
4684 
4685  if (!NT_SUCCESS(status1)) {
4686  return status1;
4687  }
4688 
4689  }
4690  else {
4691 
4692  //
4693  // This indicates the caller just wants to know the size of the
4694  // buffer to allocate but is not prepared to accept any data content
4695  // in this instance.
4696  //
4697 
4698  MappedAddress = NULL;
4699  LockVariable = NULL;
4700  }
4701 
4702  for (OpaqueSession = MmGetNextSession (NULL);
4703  OpaqueSession != NULL;
4704  OpaqueSession = MmGetNextSession (OpaqueSession)) {
4705 
4706  SessionPoolTagInfo = (PSYSTEM_SESSION_POOLTAG_INFORMATION)
4707  ((PUCHAR)MappedAddress + TotalSize);
4708 
4709  //
4710  // If a specific session was requested, only extract that one.
4711  //
4712 
4713  CurrentSessionId = MmGetSessionId (OpaqueSession);
4714 
4715  if ((*SessionId == 0xFFFFFFFF) || (CurrentSessionId == *SessionId)) {
4716 
4717  //
4718  // Attach to session now to perform operations...
4719  //
4720 
4721  if (NT_SUCCESS (MmAttachSession (OpaqueSession, &ApcState))) {
4722 
4723  //
4724  // Session is still alive so include it.
4725  //
4726 
4727  NextEntryOffset = sizeof (SYSTEM_SESSION_POOLTAG_INFORMATION);
4728  TotalSize += sizeof (SYSTEM_SESSION_POOLTAG_INFORMATION);
4729 
4730  if (TotalSize > SystemInformationLength) {
4731 
4732  status = STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
4733 
4734  //
4735  // Get absolute size for this session, ignore status as
4736  // we must return the one above.
4737  //
4738 
4739  ExGetSessionPoolTagInfo (NULL,
4740  0,
4741  &Count,
4742  &AbsoluteCount);
4743  }
4744  else {
4745 
4746  //
4747  // Get pool tagging information for each session.
4748  //
4749 
4750  status = ExGetSessionPoolTagInfo (
4751  SessionPoolTagInfo->TagInfo,
4752  SystemInformationLength - TotalSize + sizeof (SYSTEM_POOLTAG),
4753  &Count,
4754  &AbsoluteCount);
4755 
4756  SessionPoolTagInfo->SessionId = CurrentSessionId;
4757  SessionPoolTagInfo->Count = Count;
4758 
4759  //
4760  // Point to next session.
4761  //
4762 
4763  if (NT_SUCCESS (status)) {
4764  NextEntryOffset += ((Count - 1) * sizeof (SYSTEM_POOLTAG));
4765  SessionPoolTagInfo->NextEntryOffset = NextEntryOffset;
4766  }
4767  }
4768 
4769  TotalSize += ((AbsoluteCount - 1) * sizeof (SYSTEM_POOLTAG));
4770 
4771  //
4772  // Detach from session.
4773  //
4774 
4775  MmDetachSession (OpaqueSession, &ApcState);
4776  }
4777 
4778  //
4779  // Bail if only this session was of interest.
4780  //
4781 
4782  if (*SessionId != 0xFFFFFFFF) {
4783  MmQuitNextSession (OpaqueSession);
4784  break;
4785  }
4786  }
4787  }
4788 
4789  if ((NT_SUCCESS (status)) && (SessionPoolTagInfo != NULL)) {
4790  SessionPoolTagInfo->NextEntryOffset = 0;
4791  }
4792 
4793  if (MappedAddress != NULL) {
4794  ExUnlockUserBuffer (LockVariable);
4795  }
4796 
4797  *Length = TotalSize;
4798 
4799  return status;
4800 }

4802 NTSTATUS
4803 ExpGetProcessorPowerInformation (
4804  OUT PVOID SystemInformation,
4805  IN ULONG SystemInformationLength,
4806  OUT PULONG Length
4807  )
4808 {
4809  KAFFINITY currentAffinity;
4810  KAFFINITY processors;
4811  KIRQL oldIrql;
4812  PKPRCB Prcb;
4813  PPROCESSOR_POWER_STATE PState;
4814  PPROCESSOR_PERF_STATE PerfStates;
4815  PSYSTEM_PROCESSOR_POWER_INFORMATION CallerPowerInfo;
4816  SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_POWER_INFORMATION ProcessorPowerInfo;
4817  NTSTATUS Status;
4818 
4819  //
4820  // We will walk this pointer to store the user data...
4821  //
4822  CallerPowerInfo = (PSYSTEM_PROCESSOR_POWER_INFORMATION) SystemInformation;
4823 
4824  //
4825  // Check to see if we have the space for this
4826  //
4827 
4828  *Length = sizeof(SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_POWER_INFORMATION) * KeNumberProcessors;
4829 
4830  if (SystemInformationLength < sizeof(SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_POWER_INFORMATION) * KeNumberProcessors) {
4831  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
4832  }
4833 
4834  //
4835  // Lock everything down
4836  //
4837  MmLockPageableSectionByHandle (ExPageLockHandle);
4838 
4839  //
4840  // Walk the list of processors
4841  //
4842  processors = KeActiveProcessors;
4843  currentAffinity = 1;
4844  while (processors) {
4845 
4846 
4847  processors &= ~currentAffinity;
4848  KeSetSystemAffinityThread(currentAffinity);
4849  currentAffinity <<= 1;
4850 
4851 
4852  //
4853  // Get the PRCB and PowerState information
4854  //
4855  Prcb = KeGetCurrentPrcb();
4856  PState = &(Prcb->PowerState);
4857 
4858  //
4859  // Raise to DPC level to synchronize access to the data structures
4860  //
4861  KeRaiseIrql (DISPATCH_LEVEL, &oldIrql);
4862 
4863  PerfStates = PState->PerfStates;
4864 
4865  //
4866  // Grab the data that we care about
4867  //
4868  ProcessorPowerInfo.CurrentFrequency = PState->CurrentThrottle;
4869  ProcessorPowerInfo.LastBusyFrequency = PState->LastBusyPercentage;
4870  ProcessorPowerInfo.LastAdjustedBusyFrequency = PState->LastAdjustedBusyPercentage;
4871  ProcessorPowerInfo.LastC3Frequency = PState->LastC3Percentage;
4872  ProcessorPowerInfo.ProcessorMinThrottle = PState->ProcessorMinThrottle;
4873  ProcessorPowerInfo.ProcessorMaxThrottle = PState->ProcessorMaxThrottle;
4874  ProcessorPowerInfo.ErrorCount = PState->ErrorCount;
4875  ProcessorPowerInfo.RetryCount = PState->RetryCount;
4876 
4877  //
4878  // Do we have any kind of PerfStates?
4879  //
4880  if (PerfStates) {
4881 
4882  ProcessorPowerInfo.ThermalLimitFrequency = PerfStates[PState->ThermalThrottleIndex].PercentFrequency;
4883  ProcessorPowerInfo.ConstantThrottleFrequency = PerfStates[PState->KneeThrottleIndex].PercentFrequency;
4884  ProcessorPowerInfo.DegradedThrottleFrequency = PerfStates[PState->ThrottleLimitIndex].PercentFrequency;
4885 
4886  } else {
4887 
4888  ProcessorPowerInfo.ThermalLimitFrequency = 0;
4889  ProcessorPowerInfo.ConstantThrottleFrequency = 0;
4890  ProcessorPowerInfo.DegradedThrottleFrequency = 0;
4891 
4892  }
4893 
4894  ProcessorPowerInfo.CurrentFrequencyTime =
4895  UInt32x32To64(
4896  (Prcb->KernelTime + Prcb->UserTime - PState->PerfTickCount),
4897  KeMaximumIncrement
4898  );
4899  ProcessorPowerInfo.CurrentProcessorTime =
4900  UInt32x32To64(
4901  Prcb->KernelTime + Prcb->UserTime,
4902  KeMaximumIncrement
4903  );
4904  ProcessorPowerInfo.CurrentProcessorIdleTime =
4905  UInt32x32To64( Prcb->IdleThread->KernelTime, KeMaximumIncrement );
4906  ProcessorPowerInfo.LastProcessorTime =
4907  UInt32x32To64( PState->LastKernelUserTime, KeMaximumIncrement );
4908  ProcessorPowerInfo.LastProcessorIdleTime =
4909  UInt32x32To64( PState->PerfIdleTime, KeMaximumIncrement );
4910 
4911  ProcessorPowerInfo.PromotionCount = PState->PromotionCount;
4912  ProcessorPowerInfo.DemotionCount = PState->DemotionCount;
4913  ProcessorPowerInfo.NumberOfFrequencies = PState->PerfStatesCount;
4914 
4915  //
4916  // Return to the original level (should be IRQL 0)
4917  //
4918  KeLowerIrql (oldIrql);
4919 
4920  //
4921  // Copy the data to the correct place
4922  //
4923  try {
4924  RtlCopyMemory(
4925  CallerPowerInfo,
4926  &ProcessorPowerInfo,
4927  sizeof(SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_POWER_INFORMATION)
4928  );
4929  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
4930  Status = GetExceptionCode ();
4931  goto exit_revert_and_unlock;
4932  }
4933 
4934  //
4935  // Point to the next structure element
4936  //
4937  CallerPowerInfo++;
4938 
4939  }
4940 
4941  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
4942 
4943 exit_revert_and_unlock:
4944 
4945  //
4946  // Revert to the original affinity
4947  //
4948  KeRevertToUserAffinityThread();
4949 
4950  //
4951  // Unlock everything
4952 
4953  MmUnlockPageableImageSection(ExPageLockHandle);
4954 
4955  return Status;
4956 }

4958 NTSTATUS
4959 ExpGetProcessorIdleInformation (
4960  OUT PVOID SystemInformation,
4961  IN ULONG SystemInformationLength,
4962  OUT PULONG Length
4963  )
4964 {
4965  KAFFINITY currentAffinity;
4966  KAFFINITY processors;
4967  KIRQL oldIrql;
4968  LARGE_INTEGER PerfFrequency;
4969  PKPRCB Prcb;
4970  PPROCESSOR_POWER_STATE PState;
4971  PSYSTEM_PROCESSOR_IDLE_INFORMATION CallerIdleInfo;
4972  SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_IDLE_INFORMATION ProcessorIdleInfo;
4973  NTSTATUS Status;
4974 
4975  //
4976  // We will walk this pointer to store the user data...
4977  //
4978  CallerIdleInfo = (PSYSTEM_PROCESSOR_IDLE_INFORMATION) SystemInformation;
4979 
4980  *Length = sizeof(SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_IDLE_INFORMATION) * KeNumberProcessors;
4981 
4982  //
4983  // Check to see if we have the space for this
4984  //
4985  if (SystemInformationLength < sizeof(SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_IDLE_INFORMATION) * KeNumberProcessors) {
4986  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
4987  }
4988 
4989  //
4990  // We need to know what frequency the perf counters are running at
4991  //
4992  KeQueryPerformanceCounter(&PerfFrequency);
4993 
4994  //
4995  // Lock everything down
4996  //
4997  MmLockPageableSectionByHandle (ExPageLockHandle);
4998 
4999  //
5000  // Walk the list of processors
5001  //
5002  processors = KeActiveProcessors;
5003  currentAffinity = 1;
5004  while (processors) {
5005 
5006  processors &= ~currentAffinity;
5007  KeSetSystemAffinityThread(currentAffinity);
5008  currentAffinity <<= 1;
5009 
5010  //
5011  // Get the PRCB and PowerState information
5012  //
5013  Prcb = KeGetCurrentPrcb();
5014  PState = &(Prcb->PowerState);
5015 
5016  //
5017  // Raise to DPC level to synchronize access to the data structures
5018  //
5019  KeRaiseIrql (DISPATCH_LEVEL, &oldIrql);
5020 
5021 
5022  //
5023  // Grab the data that we care about
5024  //
5025  ProcessorIdleInfo.IdleTime = UInt32x32To64(Prcb->IdleThread->KernelTime,KeMaximumIncrement);
5026 
5027  //
5028  // The Cx times are kept in units of the same frequency as KeQueryPerformanceCounter
5029  // This needs to be converted to standard 100ns units.
5030  //
5031  ProcessorIdleInfo.C1Time = (PState->TotalIdleStateTime[0]*1000)/(PerfFrequency.QuadPart/10000);
5032  ProcessorIdleInfo.C2Time = (PState->TotalIdleStateTime[1]*1000)/(PerfFrequency.QuadPart/10000);
5033  ProcessorIdleInfo.C3Time = (PState->TotalIdleStateTime[2]*1000)/(PerfFrequency.QuadPart/10000);
5034 
5035  ProcessorIdleInfo.C1Transitions = PState->TotalIdleTransitions[0];
5036  ProcessorIdleInfo.C2Transitions = PState->TotalIdleTransitions[1];
5037  ProcessorIdleInfo.C3Transitions = PState->TotalIdleTransitions[2];
5038 
5039  //
5040  // Return to the original level (should be IRQL 0)
5041  //
5042  KeLowerIrql (oldIrql);
5043 
5044  //
5045  // Copy the data to the correct place
5046  //
5047  try {
5048  RtlCopyMemory(
5049  CallerIdleInfo,
5050  &ProcessorIdleInfo,
5051  sizeof(SYSTEM_PROCESSOR_IDLE_INFORMATION)
5052  );
5053  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
5054  Status = GetExceptionCode ();
5055  goto exit_revert_and_unlock;
5056  }
5057 
5058  //
5059  // Point to the next structure element
5060  //
5061  CallerIdleInfo++;
5062  }
5063 
5064  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
5065 
5066 exit_revert_and_unlock:
5067 
5068  //
5069  // Revert to the original affinity
5070  //
5071  KeRevertToUserAffinityThread();
5072 
5073  //
5074  // Unlock everything
5075  //
5076  MmUnlockPageableImageSection(ExPageLockHandle);
5077 
5078  return Status;
5079 }

5081 VOID
5082 ExpCopyProcessInfo (
5083  IN PSYSTEM_PROCESS_INFORMATION ProcessInfo,
5084  IN PEPROCESS Process,
5085  IN BOOLEAN ExtendedInformation
5086  )
5087 
5088 {
5089 
5090  KPROCESS_VALUES Values;
5091 
5092  PAGED_CODE();
5093 
5094  ProcessInfo->HandleCount = ObGetProcessHandleCount (Process);
5095  ProcessInfo->CreateTime = Process->CreateTime;
5096  ProcessInfo->BasePriority = Process->Pcb.BasePriority;
5097  ProcessInfo->UniqueProcessId = Process->UniqueProcessId;
5098  ProcessInfo->InheritedFromUniqueProcessId = Process->InheritedFromUniqueProcessId;
5099  ProcessInfo->PeakVirtualSize = Process->PeakVirtualSize;
5100  ProcessInfo->VirtualSize = Process->VirtualSize;
5101  ProcessInfo->PageFaultCount = Process->Vm.PageFaultCount;
5102  ProcessInfo->PeakWorkingSetSize = ((SIZE_T)Process->Vm.PeakWorkingSetSize) << PAGE_SHIFT;
5103  ProcessInfo->WorkingSetSize = ((SIZE_T)Process->Vm.WorkingSetSize) << PAGE_SHIFT;
5104  ProcessInfo->QuotaPeakPagedPoolUsage =
5105  Process->QuotaPeak[PsPagedPool];
5106 
5107  ProcessInfo->QuotaPagedPoolUsage = Process->QuotaUsage[PsPagedPool];
5108  ProcessInfo->QuotaPeakNonPagedPoolUsage =
5109  Process->QuotaPeak[PsNonPagedPool];
5110 
5111  ProcessInfo->QuotaNonPagedPoolUsage =
5112  Process->QuotaUsage[PsNonPagedPool];
5113 
5114  ProcessInfo->PagefileUsage = Process->QuotaUsage[PsPageFile] << PAGE_SHIFT;
5115  ProcessInfo->PeakPagefileUsage = Process->QuotaPeak[PsPageFile] << PAGE_SHIFT;
5116  ProcessInfo->PrivatePageCount = Process->CommitCharge << PAGE_SHIFT;
5117 
5118  //
5119  // Query the process kernel runtime, user runtime, and I/O statistics.
5120  //
5121 
5122  KeQueryValuesProcess(&Process->Pcb, &Values);
5123  ProcessInfo->UserTime.QuadPart = Values.UserTime;
5124  ProcessInfo->KernelTime.QuadPart = Values.KernelTime;
5125  ProcessInfo->ReadOperationCount.QuadPart = Values.ReadOperationCount;
5126  ProcessInfo->WriteOperationCount.QuadPart = Values.WriteOperationCount;
5127  ProcessInfo->OtherOperationCount.QuadPart = Values.OtherOperationCount;
5128  ProcessInfo->ReadTransferCount.QuadPart = Values.ReadTransferCount;
5129  ProcessInfo->WriteTransferCount.QuadPart = Values.WriteTransferCount;
5130  ProcessInfo->OtherTransferCount.QuadPart = Values.OtherTransferCount;
5131  if (ExtendedInformation) {
5132  ProcessInfo->PageDirectoryBase = MmGetDirectoryFrameFromProcess(Process);
5133  }
5134 }

5136 VOID
5137 ExpCopyThreadInfo (
5138  IN PVOID ThreadInfoBuffer,
5139  IN PETHREAD Thread,
5140  IN BOOLEAN ExtendedInformation
5141  )
5142 
5143 /*++
5144 
5145 Routine Description:
5146 
5147  This function returns information about the specified thread.
5148 
5149 Arguments:
5150 
5151  ThreadInfoBuffer - A pointer to a buffer which receives the specified
5152  information.
5153 
5154  Thread - Supplies a pointer to the desired thread.
5155 
5156  ExtendedInformation - TRUE if extended thread information is needed.
5157 
5158 Environment:
5159 
5160  Kernel mode. The dispatcher lock is held.
5161 
5162  This routine could be made PAGELK but it is a high frequency routine
5163  so it is actually better to keep it nonpaged to avoid bringing in the
5164  entire PAGELK section.
5165 
5166 Return Value:
5167 
5168  None.
5169 
5170 --*/
5171 
5172 {
5173  PSYSTEM_THREAD_INFORMATION ThreadInfo;
5174  ThreadInfo = (PSYSTEM_THREAD_INFORMATION) ThreadInfoBuffer;
5175 
5176  ThreadInfo->KernelTime.QuadPart = UInt32x32To64(Thread->Tcb.KernelTime,
5177  KeMaximumIncrement);
5178 
5179  ThreadInfo->UserTime.QuadPart = UInt32x32To64(Thread->Tcb.UserTime,
5180  KeMaximumIncrement);
5181 
5182  ThreadInfo->CreateTime.QuadPart = PS_GET_THREAD_CREATE_TIME (Thread);
5183  ThreadInfo->WaitTime = Thread->Tcb.WaitTime;
5184  ThreadInfo->ClientId = Thread->Cid;
5185  ThreadInfo->ThreadState = Thread->Tcb.State;
5186  ThreadInfo->WaitReason = Thread->Tcb.WaitReason;
5187  ThreadInfo->Priority = Thread->Tcb.Priority;
5188  ThreadInfo->BasePriority = Thread->Tcb.BasePriority;
5189  ThreadInfo->ContextSwitches = Thread->Tcb.ContextSwitches;
5190  ThreadInfo->StartAddress = Thread->StartAddress;
5191 
5192  if (ExtendedInformation) {
5193  PSYSTEM_EXTENDED_THREAD_INFORMATION ExtendedThreadInfo;
5194 
5195  ExtendedThreadInfo = (PSYSTEM_EXTENDED_THREAD_INFORMATION) ThreadInfo;
5196 
5197  ExtendedThreadInfo->StackBase = Thread->Tcb.StackBase;
5198  ExtendedThreadInfo->StackLimit = Thread->Tcb.StackLimit;
5199  if (Thread->LpcReceivedMsgIdValid) {
5200  ExtendedThreadInfo->Win32StartAddress = 0;
5201  } else {
5202  ExtendedThreadInfo->Win32StartAddress = Thread->Win32StartAddress;
5203  }
5204  ExtendedThreadInfo->Reserved1 = 0;
5205  ExtendedThreadInfo->Reserved2 = 0;
5206  ExtendedThreadInfo->Reserved3 = 0;
5207  ExtendedThreadInfo->Reserved4 = 0;
5208  }
5209 
5210 }

5213 
5214 extern ULONG ExVdmOpcodeDispatchCounts[256];
5215 extern ULONG VdmBopCount;
5216 extern ULONG ExVdmSegmentNotPresent;
5217

5271 NTSTATUS
5272 ExpGetStackTraceInformation (
5273  OUT PVOID SystemInformation,
5274  IN ULONG SystemInformationLength,
5275  OUT PULONG ReturnLength OPTIONAL
5276  )
5277 {
5278  NTSTATUS Status;
5279  PRTL_PROCESS_BACKTRACES BackTraceInformation;
5280  PRTL_PROCESS_BACKTRACE_INFORMATION BackTraceInfo;
5281  PSTACK_TRACE_DATABASE DataBase;
5282  PRTL_STACK_TRACE_ENTRY p, *pp;
5283  ULONG RequiredLength, n;
5284 
5285  DataBase = RtlpAcquireStackTraceDataBase();
5286 
5287  if (DataBase == NULL) {
5288  return STATUS_UNSUCCESSFUL;
5289  }
5290  DataBase->DumpInProgress = TRUE;
5291 
5292  RtlpReleaseStackTraceDataBase();
5293 
5294  n = 0;
5295  RequiredLength = 0;
5296  Status = STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
5297  BackTraceInformation = (PRTL_PROCESS_BACKTRACES) SystemInformation;
5298 
5299  RequiredLength = FIELD_OFFSET( RTL_PROCESS_BACKTRACES, BackTraces );
5300 
5301  try {
5302  if (SystemInformationLength >= RequiredLength) {
5303  BackTraceInformation->CommittedMemory =
5304  (ULONG)DataBase->CurrentUpperCommitLimit - (ULONG)DataBase->CommitBase;
5305  BackTraceInformation->ReservedMemory =
5306  (ULONG)DataBase->EntryIndexArray - (ULONG)DataBase->CommitBase;
5307  BackTraceInformation->NumberOfBackTraceLookups = DataBase->NumberOfEntriesLookedUp;
5308  n = DataBase->NumberOfEntriesAdded;
5309  BackTraceInformation->NumberOfBackTraces = n;
5310  }
5311 
5312  RequiredLength += (sizeof( *BackTraceInfo ) * n);
5313  if (SystemInformationLength >= RequiredLength) {
5314  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
5315  BackTraceInfo = &BackTraceInformation->BackTraces[ 0 ];
5316  pp = DataBase->EntryIndexArray;
5317  while (n--) {
5318  p = *--pp;
5319  BackTraceInfo->SymbolicBackTrace = NULL;
5320  BackTraceInfo->TraceCount = p->TraceCount;
5321  BackTraceInfo->Index = p->Index;
5322  BackTraceInfo->Depth = p->Depth;
5323  RtlCopyMemory( BackTraceInfo->BackTrace,
5324  p->BackTrace,
5325  p->Depth * sizeof( PVOID )
5326  );
5327  BackTraceInfo += 1;
5328  }
5329  }
5330  }
5331  finally {
5332  DataBase->DumpInProgress = FALSE;
5333  }
5334 
5335  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(ReturnLength)) {
5336  *ReturnLength = RequiredLength;
5337  }
5338  return Status;
5339 }
