5343 NTSTATUS
5344 ExpGetLockInformation (
5345  OUT PVOID SystemInformation,
5346  IN ULONG SystemInformationLength,
5347  OUT PULONG Length
5348  )
5349 
5350 /*++
5351 
5352 Routine Description:
5353 
5354  This function returns information about all the ERESOURCE locks
5355  in the system.
5356 
5357 Arguments:
5358 
5359  SystemInformation - A pointer to a buffer which receives the specified
5360  information.
5361 
5362  SystemInformationLength - Specifies the length in bytes of the system
5363  information buffer.
5364 
5365  Length - An optional pointer which, if specified, receives the
5366  number of bytes placed in the system information buffer.
5367 
5368 
5369 Return Value:
5370 
5371  Returns one of the following status codes:
5372 
5373  STATUS_SUCCESS - normal, successful completion.
5374 
5375  STATUS_INVALID_INFO_CLASS - The SystemInformationClass parameter
5376  did not specify a valid value.
5377 
5378  STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH - The value of the SystemInformationLength
5379  parameter did not match the length required for the information
5380  class requested by the SystemInformationClass parameter.
5381 
5382  STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION - Either the SystemInformation buffer pointer
5383  or the Length pointer value specified an invalid address.
5384 
5385  STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA - The process does not have sufficient
5386  working set to lock the specified output structure in memory.
5387 
5388  STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES - Insufficient system resources exist
5389  for this request to complete.
5390 
5391 --*/
5392 
5393 {
5394  PRTL_PROCESS_LOCKS LockInfo;
5395  PVOID LockVariable;
5396  NTSTATUS Status;
5397 
5398  *Length = 0;
5399 
5400  Status = ExLockUserBuffer( SystemInformation,
5401  SystemInformationLength,
5402  KeGetPreviousMode(),
5403  IoWriteAccess,
5404  &LockInfo,
5405  &LockVariable
5406  );
5407  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
5408  return( Status );
5409  }
5410 
5411  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
5412 
5413  MmLockPageableSectionByHandle (ExPageLockHandle);
5414  try {
5415 
5416  Status = ExQuerySystemLockInformation( LockInfo,
5417  SystemInformationLength,
5418  Length
5419  );
5420  }
5421  finally {
5422  ExUnlockUserBuffer( LockVariable );
5423  MmUnlockPageableImageSection(ExPageLockHandle);
5424  }
5425 
5426  return Status;
5427 }

5429 NTSTATUS
5430 ExpGetLookasideInformation (
5431  OUT PVOID Buffer,
5432  IN ULONG BufferLength,
5433  OUT PULONG Length
5434  )
5435 
5436 /*++
5437 
5438 Routine Description:
5439 
5440  This function returns pool lookaside list and general lookaside
5441  list information.
5442 
5443 Arguments:
5444 
5445  Buffer - Supplies a pointer to the buffer which receives the lookaside
5446  list information.
5447 
5448  BufferLength - Supplies the length of the information buffer in bytes.
5449 
5450  Length - Supplies a pointer to a variable that receives the length of
5451  lookaside information returned.
5452 
5453 Environment:
5454 
5455  Kernel mode.
5456 
5457  This routine could be made PAGELK but it is a high frequency routine
5458  so it is actually better to keep it nonpaged to avoid bringing in the
5459  entire PAGELK section.
5460 
5461 Return Value:
5462 
5463  Returns one of the following status codes:
5464 
5465  STATUS_SUCCESS - Normal, successful completion.
5466 
5467  STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION - The buffer could not be locked in memory.
5468 
5469 --*/
5470 
5471 {
5472 
5473  PVOID BufferLock;
5474  PLIST_ENTRY Entry;
5475  KIRQL OldIrql;
5476  ULONG Limit;
5477  PSYSTEM_LOOKASIDE_INFORMATION Lookaside;
5478  ULONG Number;
5479  PNPAGED_LOOKASIDE_LIST NPagedLookaside;
5480  PPAGED_LOOKASIDE_LIST PagedLookaside;
5481  PGENERAL_LOOKASIDE PoolLookaside;
5482  PGENERAL_LOOKASIDE SystemLookaside;
5483  PKSPIN_LOCK SpinLock;
5484  NTSTATUS Status;
5485 
5486  //
5487  // Compute the number of lookaside entries and set the return status to
5488  // success.
5489  //
5490 
5491  Limit = BufferLength / sizeof(SYSTEM_LOOKASIDE_INFORMATION);
5492  Number = 0;
5493  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
5494 
5495  //
5496  // If the number of lookaside entries to return is not zero, then collect
5497  // the lookaside information.
5498  //
5499 
5500  if (Limit != 0) {
5501  Status = ExLockUserBuffer(Buffer,
5502  BufferLength,
5503  KeGetPreviousMode(),
5504  IoWriteAccess,
5505  &Lookaside,
5506  &BufferLock);
5507  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
5508 
5509  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
5510 
5511  //
5512  // Copy nonpaged and paged pool lookaside information to
5513  // information buffer.
5514  //
5515 
5516  Entry = ExPoolLookasideListHead.Flink;
5517  while (Entry != &ExPoolLookasideListHead) {
5518  PoolLookaside = CONTAINING_RECORD(Entry,
5519  GENERAL_LOOKASIDE,
5520  ListEntry);
5521 
5522  Lookaside->CurrentDepth = ExQueryDepthSList(&PoolLookaside->ListHead);
5523  Lookaside->MaximumDepth = PoolLookaside->Depth;
5524  Lookaside->TotalAllocates = PoolLookaside->TotalAllocates;
5525  Lookaside->AllocateMisses =
5526  PoolLookaside->TotalAllocates - PoolLookaside->AllocateHits;
5527 
5528  Lookaside->TotalFrees = PoolLookaside->TotalFrees;
5529  Lookaside->FreeMisses =
5530  PoolLookaside->TotalFrees - PoolLookaside->FreeHits;
5531 
5532  Lookaside->Type = PoolLookaside->Type;
5533  Lookaside->Tag = PoolLookaside->Tag;
5534  Lookaside->Size = PoolLookaside->Size;
5535  Number += 1;
5536  if (Number == Limit) {
5537  goto Finish2;
5538  }
5539 
5540  Entry = Entry->Flink;
5541  Lookaside += 1;
5542  }
5543 
5544  //
5545  // Copy nonpaged and paged system lookaside information to
5546  // information buffer.
5547  //
5548 
5549  Entry = ExSystemLookasideListHead.Flink;
5550  while (Entry != &ExSystemLookasideListHead) {
5551  SystemLookaside = CONTAINING_RECORD(Entry,
5552  GENERAL_LOOKASIDE,
5553  ListEntry);
5554 
5555  Lookaside->CurrentDepth = ExQueryDepthSList(&SystemLookaside->ListHead);
5556  Lookaside->MaximumDepth = SystemLookaside->Depth;
5557  Lookaside->TotalAllocates = SystemLookaside->TotalAllocates;
5558  Lookaside->AllocateMisses = SystemLookaside->AllocateMisses;
5559  Lookaside->TotalFrees = SystemLookaside->TotalFrees;
5560  Lookaside->FreeMisses = SystemLookaside->FreeMisses;
5561  Lookaside->Type = SystemLookaside->Type;
5562  Lookaside->Tag = SystemLookaside->Tag;
5563  Lookaside->Size = SystemLookaside->Size;
5564  Number += 1;
5565  if (Number == Limit) {
5566  goto Finish2;
5567  }
5568 
5569  Entry = Entry->Flink;
5570  Lookaside += 1;
5571  }
5572 
5573  //
5574  // Copy nonpaged general lookaside information to buffer.
5575  //
5576 
5577  SpinLock = &ExNPagedLookasideLock;
5578  ExAcquireSpinLock(SpinLock, &OldIrql);
5579  Entry = ExNPagedLookasideListHead.Flink;
5580  while (Entry != &ExNPagedLookasideListHead) {
5581  NPagedLookaside = CONTAINING_RECORD(Entry,
5582  NPAGED_LOOKASIDE_LIST,
5583  L.ListEntry);
5584 
5585  Lookaside->CurrentDepth = ExQueryDepthSList(&NPagedLookaside->L.ListHead);
5586  Lookaside->MaximumDepth = NPagedLookaside->L.Depth;
5587  Lookaside->TotalAllocates = NPagedLookaside->L.TotalAllocates;
5588  Lookaside->AllocateMisses = NPagedLookaside->L.AllocateMisses;
5589  Lookaside->TotalFrees = NPagedLookaside->L.TotalFrees;
5590  Lookaside->FreeMisses = NPagedLookaside->L.FreeMisses;
5591  Lookaside->Type = 0;
5592  Lookaside->Tag = NPagedLookaside->L.Tag;
5593  Lookaside->Size = NPagedLookaside->L.Size;
5594  Number += 1;
5595  if (Number == Limit) {
5596  goto Finish1;
5597  }
5598 
5599  Entry = Entry->Flink;
5600  Lookaside += 1;
5601  }
5602 
5603  ExReleaseSpinLock(SpinLock, OldIrql);
5604 
5605  //
5606  // Copy paged general lookaside information to buffer.
5607  //
5608 
5609  SpinLock = &ExPagedLookasideLock;
5610  ExAcquireSpinLock(SpinLock, &OldIrql);
5611  Entry = ExPagedLookasideListHead.Flink;
5612  while (Entry != &ExPagedLookasideListHead) {
5613  PagedLookaside = CONTAINING_RECORD(Entry,
5614  PAGED_LOOKASIDE_LIST,
5615  L.ListEntry);
5616 
5617  Lookaside->CurrentDepth = ExQueryDepthSList(&PagedLookaside->L.ListHead);
5618  Lookaside->MaximumDepth = PagedLookaside->L.Depth;
5619  Lookaside->TotalAllocates = PagedLookaside->L.TotalAllocates;
5620  Lookaside->AllocateMisses = PagedLookaside->L.AllocateMisses;
5621  Lookaside->TotalFrees = PagedLookaside->L.TotalFrees;
5622  Lookaside->FreeMisses = PagedLookaside->L.FreeMisses;
5623  Lookaside->Type = 1;
5624  Lookaside->Tag = PagedLookaside->L.Tag;
5625  Lookaside->Size = PagedLookaside->L.Size;
5626  Number += 1;
5627  if (Number == Limit) {
5628  goto Finish1;
5629  }
5630 
5631  Entry = Entry->Flink;
5632  Lookaside += 1;
5633  }
5634 
5635 Finish1:
5636  ExReleaseSpinLock(SpinLock, OldIrql);
5637 
5638 Finish2:
5639  //
5640  // Unlock user buffer.
5641  //
5642 
5643  ExUnlockUserBuffer(BufferLock);
5644  }
5645  }
5646 
5647  *Length = Number * sizeof(SYSTEM_LOOKASIDE_INFORMATION);
5648  return Status;
5649 }

5652 ExpGetHandleInformation (

5655  OUT PULONG Length
5656  )
5657 
5658 /*++

5660 Routine Description:

5712  IoWriteAccess,
5713  &HandleInfo,
5714  &LockVariable
5715  );

5718  }

5724  SystemInformationLength,
5725  Length
5726  );
5727 
5728  }
5729  finally {

5731  }
5732 
5733  return Status;
5734 }

5907 NTSTATUS
5908 ExpQueryModuleInformation (
5909  IN PLIST_ENTRY LoadOrderListHead,
5910  IN PLIST_ENTRY UserModeLoadOrderListHead,
5911  OUT PRTL_PROCESS_MODULES ModuleInformation,
5912  IN ULONG ModuleInformationLength,
5913  OUT PULONG ReturnLength OPTIONAL
5914  )
5915 {
5916  NTSTATUS Status;
5917  ULONG RequiredLength;
5918  PLIST_ENTRY Next;
5919  PRTL_PROCESS_MODULE_INFORMATION ModuleInfo;
5920  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY LdrDataTableEntry;
5921  ANSI_STRING AnsiString;
5922  PCHAR s;
5923  ULONG NumberOfModules;
5924 
5925  NumberOfModules = 0;
5926  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
5927  RequiredLength = FIELD_OFFSET( RTL_PROCESS_MODULES, Modules );
5928  ModuleInfo = &ModuleInformation->Modules[ 0 ];
5929 
5930  Next = LoadOrderListHead->Flink;
5931  while ( Next != LoadOrderListHead ) {
5932  LdrDataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD( Next,
5933  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
5934  InLoadOrderLinks
5935  );
5936 
5937  RequiredLength += sizeof( RTL_PROCESS_MODULE_INFORMATION );
5938  if (ModuleInformationLength < RequiredLength) {
5939  Status = STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;

6046 BOOLEAN
6047 ExIsProcessorFeaturePresent (
6048  __in ULONG ProcessorFeature
6049  )
6050 
6051 {
6052 
6053  BOOLEAN rv;
6054 
6055  //
6056  // On AMD64 systems legacy floating point, MMX, and 3D-Now are not
6057  // supported for 64-bit applications (i.e., the legacy floating
6058  // point state is not saved and restored). Therefore, FALSE is always
6059  // returned for these features.
6060  //
6061 
6062 #if defined(_AMD64_)
6063 
6064  if ((ProcessorFeature == PF_MMX_INSTRUCTIONS_AVAILABLE) ||
6065  (ProcessorFeature == PF_3DNOW_INSTRUCTIONS_AVAILABLE)) {
6066 
6067  return FALSE;
6068  }
6069 
6070 #endif
6071 
6072  if (ProcessorFeature < PROCESSOR_FEATURE_MAX) {
6073  rv = SharedUserData->ProcessorFeatures[ProcessorFeature];
6074 
6075  } else {
6076  rv = FALSE;
6077  }
6078 
6079  return rv;
6080 }

6285 NTSTATUS
6286 ExpGetSystemFirmwareTableInformation(
6287  IN OUT PVOID SystemFirmwareTableInformation,
6288  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode,
6289  OUT PULONG ReturnLength OPTIONAL
6290  )
6291 
6292 /*++
6293 
6294 Description:
6295 
6296  Look for the requested Firmware Table provider. if it exists, pass the
6297  request on to it and return the result.
6298 
6299 Parameters:
6300 
6301  SystemFirmwareTableInformation - points to the SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_INFORMATION
6302  structure.
6303 
6304  ReturnLength - returns the bufferlength if present.
6305 
6306 Return Value:
6307 
6308  STATUS_SUCCESS - on success.
6309  STATUS_NOT_IMPLEMENTED - on Failure.
6310 
6311 --*/
6312 
6313 {
6314  ULONG BufferLength = 0;
6315  PSYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_HANDLER_NODE HandlerCurrent;
6316  NTSTATUS Status = STATUS_NOT_IMPLEMENTED;
6317  PSYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_INFORMATION TableInfo = NULL;
6318  PSYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_INFORMATION TableInfoLocal = NULL;
6319  ULONG TotalStructSize = 0;
6320 
6321  PAGED_CODE();
6322 
6323  //
6324  // Point the incoming SystemFirmwareTableInformation to TableInfo. If this
6325  // is a usermode call, we will copy all the usermode data into local buffers
6326  // before calling the table provider.
6327  //
6328 
6329  TableInfo = (PSYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_INFORMATION)SystemFirmwareTableInformation;
6330 
6331  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
6332 
6333  try {
6334 
6335  ProbeForRead(&(TableInfo->TableBufferLength),
6336  sizeof(ULONG),
6337  sizeof(ULONG));
6338 
6339  //
6340  // Save a copy of the TableBufferLength as this value may be changed
6341  // by the table providers handler.
6342  //
6343 
6344  BufferLength = TableInfo->TableBufferLength;
6345 
6346  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
6347 
6348  return GetExceptionCode();
6349  }
6350 
6351  TotalStructSize = sizeof(SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_INFORMATION) + BufferLength;
6352 
6353  //
6354  // Allocate a local buffer. This way we always pass trusted memory to the
6355  // firmware table providers.
6356  //
6357 
6358  TableInfoLocal = ExAllocatePoolWithQuotaTag(PagedPool,
6359  TotalStructSize,
6360  'TFRA');
6361 
6362  if (!TableInfoLocal) {
6363 
6364  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
6365  }
6366 
6367  RtlZeroMemory(TableInfoLocal, TotalStructSize);
6368 
6369  try {
6370 
6371  //
6372  // Verify and copy the data to trusted memory.
6373  //
6374 
6375  ProbeForRead(TableInfo,
6376  sizeof(SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_INFORMATION),
6377  sizeof(ULONG));
6378 
6379  RtlCopyMemory(TableInfoLocal,
6380  TableInfo,
6381  sizeof(SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_INFORMATION));
6382  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
6383 
6384  return GetExceptionCode();
6385  }
6386 
6387  //
6388  // Now save a pointer to our copy of TableInfoLocal into Tableinfo. This
6389  // will improve code readability because all the shared code between user
6390  // mode and kernel mode will use the same variable name.
6391  //
6392 
6393  TableInfo = TableInfoLocal;
6394  }
6395 
6396  //
6397  // Grab the resource as shared.
6398  //
6399 
6400  KeEnterCriticalRegion();
6401 
6402  ExAcquireResourceSharedLite(&ExpFirmwareTableResource, TRUE);
6403 
6404  //
6405  // Check if the required table provider is available.
6406  //
6407 
6408  EX_FOR_EACH_IN_LIST(SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_HANDLER_NODE,
6409  FirmwareTableProviderList,
6410  &ExpFirmwareTableProviderListHead,
6411  HandlerCurrent) {
6412 
6413  if (HandlerCurrent->SystemFWHandler.ProviderSignature == TableInfo->ProviderSignature) {
6414 
6415  //
6416  // Call the providers handler.
6417  //
6418 
6419  Status = (*(HandlerCurrent->SystemFWHandler.FirmwareTableHandler))(TableInfo);
6420 
6421  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
6422 
6423  //
6424  // Copy the returned data to the callers buffer.
6425  //
6426 
6427  try {
6428 
6429  //
6430  // Point Tableinfo back to the original usermode buffer. Our
6431  // new data is safe in TableInfoLocal.
6432  //
6433 
6434  TableInfo = (PSYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_INFORMATION)
6435  SystemFirmwareTableInformation;
6436 
6437 
6438  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
6439 
6440  //
6441  // The usermode buffer (stored in TableInfo) in untrusted.
6442  // It's content could have changed. Use the cached value
6443  // in BufferLength to do the probe and make sure the
6444  // buffer is still valid.
6445 
6446  //
6447  // Probe the Table buffer for writing.
6448  //
6449 
6450  ProbeForWrite(TableInfo->TableBuffer,
6451  BufferLength,
6452  sizeof(UCHAR));
6453 
6454  //
6455  // Copy over the returned buffer to the user mode buffer.
6456  //
6457 
6458  RtlCopyMemory(TableInfo->TableBuffer,
6459  TableInfoLocal->TableBuffer,
6460  TableInfoLocal->TableBufferLength);
6461  }
6462 
6463  //
6464  // Always update the returned buffer length.
6465  //
6466 
6467  //
6468  // Probe the structure for writing.
6469  //
6470 
6471  ProbeForWrite(&(TableInfo->TableBufferLength),
6472  sizeof(ULONG),
6473  sizeof(ULONG));
6474 
6475  //
6476  // Copy over the number of bytes written or required.
6477  //
6478 
6479  RtlCopyMemory(&(TableInfo->TableBufferLength),
6480  &(TableInfoLocal->TableBufferLength),
6481  sizeof(ULONG));
6482 
6483  TableInfo = TableInfoLocal;
6484 
6485  //
6486  // Fill in ReturnLength.
6487  //
6488 
6489  if (ReturnLength) {
6490 
6491  ProbeForWrite(ReturnLength,
6492  sizeof(ULONG),
6493  sizeof(ULONG));
6494 
6495  *ReturnLength = TableInfo->TableBufferLength +
6496  sizeof(SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_INFORMATION);
6497  }
6498 
6499 
6500  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
6501 
6502  Status = GetExceptionCode();
6503  }
6504 
6505  } else {
6506 
6507  //
6508  // Fill in ReturnLength.
6509  //
6510  if (ReturnLength) {
6511 
6512  *ReturnLength = TableInfo->TableBufferLength +
6513  sizeof(SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_INFORMATION);
6514  }
6515  }
6516 
6517  break;
6518  }
6519  }
6520 
6521  if (TableInfoLocal) {
6522 
6523  ExFreePoolWithTag(TableInfoLocal, 'TFRA');
6524  }
6525 
6526  ExReleaseResourceLite(&ExpFirmwareTableResource);
6527 
6528  KeLeaveCriticalRegion();
6529 
6530  return Status;
6531 }

6534 NTSTATUS
6535 ExpRegisterFirmwareTableInformationHandler(
6536  IN OUT PVOID SystemInformation,
6537  IN ULONG SystemInformationLength,
6538  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode
6539  )
6540 
6541 /*++
6542 
6543 Description:
6544 
6545  This routine registers and unregisters firmware table providers.
6546 
6547 Parameters:
6548 
6549  SystemInformation - points to the SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_HANDLER
6550  structure.
6551 
6552  SystemInformationLength - returns the number of bytes written on success. if
6553  the provided buffer was too small, it returns the
6554  required size.
6555 
6556  PreviousMode - Previous mode (Kernel / User).
6557 
6558 Return Value:
6559 
6560  STATUS_SUCCESS - On success.
6561  STATUS_PRIVILEGE_NOT_HELD - If caller is from User mode.
6562  STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH - Buffer too small.
6563  STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES - On failure to allocate resources.
6564  STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_EXISTS - Table already registered.
6565  STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER - Table not found / invalid request.
6566 
6567 --*/
6568 
6569 {
6570 
6571  BOOLEAN HandlerFound = FALSE;
6572  PSYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_HANDLER_NODE HandlerListCurrent = NULL;
6573  PSYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_HANDLER_NODE HandlerListNew = NULL;
6574  NTSTATUS Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
6575  PSYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_HANDLER SystemTableHandler = NULL;
6576 
6577  PAGED_CODE();
6578 
6579  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
6580 
6581  Status = STATUS_PRIVILEGE_NOT_HELD;
6582  } else {
6583 
6584  if ((!SystemInformation) ||
6585  (SystemInformationLength < sizeof(SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_HANDLER))) {
6586 
6587  Status = STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
6588  } else {
6589 
6590  //
6591  // Grab the resource to prevent state change via reentry.
6592  //
6593 
6594  KeEnterCriticalRegion();
6595 
6596  ExAcquireResourceExclusiveLite(&ExpFirmwareTableResource,
6597  TRUE);
6598 
6599  SystemTableHandler = (PSYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_HANDLER)SystemInformation;
6600 
6601  EX_FOR_EACH_IN_LIST(SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_HANDLER_NODE,
6602  FirmwareTableProviderList,
6603  &ExpFirmwareTableProviderListHead,
6604  HandlerListCurrent) {
6605 
6606  if (HandlerListCurrent->SystemFWHandler.ProviderSignature == SystemTableHandler->ProviderSignature) {
6607 
6608  HandlerFound = TRUE;
6609  break;
6610  }
6611  }
6612 
6613  //
6614  // Handler was not found and this is a register request, so
6615  // allocate a new node and insert it into the list.
6616  //
6617 
6618  if ((!HandlerFound) && (SystemTableHandler->Register)) {
6619 
6620  //
6621  // This is a new Firmware table handler, allocate
6622  // the space and add it to the list.
6623  //
6624 
6625  HandlerListNew = ExAllocatePoolWithTag(PagedPool,
6626  sizeof(SYSTEM_FIRMWARE_TABLE_HANDLER_NODE),
6627  'TFRA');
6628 
6629  if (HandlerListNew) {
6630 
6631  //
6632  // Populate the new node.
6633  //
6634 
6635  HandlerListNew->SystemFWHandler.ProviderSignature = SystemTableHandler->ProviderSignature;
6636 
6637  HandlerListNew->SystemFWHandler.FirmwareTableHandler = SystemTableHandler->FirmwareTableHandler;
6638 
6639  HandlerListNew->SystemFWHandler.DriverObject = SystemTableHandler->DriverObject;
6640 
6641  InitializeListHead(&HandlerListNew->FirmwareTableProviderList);
6642 
6643  //
6644  // Grab a reference to the providers driverobject so that the
6645  // driver does not get unloaded without our knowledge. The
6646  // handler must first be unregistered before unloading.
6647  //
6648 
6649  ObReferenceObject((PVOID)HandlerListNew->SystemFWHandler.DriverObject);
6650 
6651  //
6652  // Update the LinkList.
6653  //
6654 
6655  InsertTailList(&ExpFirmwareTableProviderListHead,
6656  &HandlerListNew->FirmwareTableProviderList);
6657  } else {
6658 
6659  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
6660  }
6661 
6662  } else if ((HandlerFound) && (!(SystemTableHandler->Register))) {
6663 
6664 
6665  //
6666  // Check to make sure that a matching driver object was sent in.
6667  //
6668 
6669  if (HandlerListCurrent->SystemFWHandler.DriverObject == SystemTableHandler->DriverObject) {
6670 
6671  //
6672  // Remove the entry from the list.
6673  //
6674 
6675  RemoveEntryList(&HandlerListCurrent->FirmwareTableProviderList);
6676 
6677  //
6678  // Deref the device object.
6679  //
6680 
6681  ObDereferenceObject((PVOID)HandlerListCurrent->SystemFWHandler.DriverObject);
6682 
6683  //
6684  // Free the unregistered list element.
6685  //
6686 
6687  ExFreePoolWithTag(HandlerListCurrent, 'TFRA');
6688  } else {
6689 
6690  Status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
6691 
6692  }
6693  } else if ((HandlerFound) && (SystemTableHandler->Register)) {
6694 
6695  //
6696  // A handler for this table has already been registered. return
6697  // error.
6698  //
6699 
6700  Status = STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_EXISTS;
6701  } else {
6702 
6703  Status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
6704  }
6705 
6706  ExReleaseResourceLite(&ExpFirmwareTableResource);
6707 
6708  KeLeaveCriticalRegion();
6709  }
6710  }
6711 
6712  return Status;
6713 }
